Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.37,0:02:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The first principle we're talking about today, that nothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.48,0:02:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The first illusion, the illusion that holds back most of the people in an audience such as this,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world such as this, Chicago calibrates at 430, that is very advanced, relatively advanced intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.14,0:02:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that holds people back is the belief in causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.62,0:02:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the thought that something out there is causing, responsible for, blamed for, should be punished for,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.92,0:03:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,arrested and imprisoned, or thrown into hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is causing everything to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.30,0:03:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We spend our lifetime looking for the culprits,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and that belief system is the very foundation of the Trial Lawyers Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.66,0:03:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Our court system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.63,0:03:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That something is causing something out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.14,0:03:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and all we have to do is find it, punish it, and life will get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.87,0:03:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the world, you see how causality sets the world up into the duality of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.65,0:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Belief in causality sets up a perpetrator and a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.54,0:03:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It creates endless contention and war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.36,0:04:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If something is causing something, it's based on an illusion because the intellect lacks humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.54,0:04:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't actually know at all why anything is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.64,0:04:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hasn't got the slightest idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.86,0:04:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But it can't handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the child says to the teacher, why does the flower turn around and follow the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.82,0:04:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher says, heliotropism.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.70,0:04:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The child says, oh, he doesn't even know any more than he did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.70,0:04:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither does the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.10,0:04:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You still don't know why the flower follows the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the interjection of pseudo, pseudo-knowledge is the specialty of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus we have creation versus evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.87,0:05:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to explain how phenomena occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.27,0:05:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the explanation of evolution, you see, is causal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.10,0:05:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the billiard balls, A, B, C, D, E, all hitting each other in a sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.14,0:05:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality, as an explanation for the phenomena of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates, in my vernacular, at a miserable 450 or 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.35,0:05:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality calibrates around 450, 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Newton's law of evolution calibrates around 450, 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Newton's law of evolution calibrates around 450, 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Newton's law of evolution calibrates around 450, 455, 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.11,0:05:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his name? Darwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin's law of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.05,0:06:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.15,0:06:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality on our calibrated scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.15,0:06:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which we'll get to as soon as we have the machinery set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the middle of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.69,0:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is the middle of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.36,0:06:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is the middle of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.67,0:06:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people in our world ever transcend the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people in our world ever transcend the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit, love, the subjective reality of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect calibrates in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit, love, the subjective reality of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.56,0:06:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,really starts at 500, which is love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.56,0:06:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,really starts at 500, which is love.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.97,0:06:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The other downside of the belief in causality
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.97,0:06:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is first of all it's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.97,0:06:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is first of all it's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.23,0:06:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the pathway I teach, called devotional non-duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.23,0:06:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is to transcend duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.23,0:06:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is to transcend duality,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.40,0:07:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you believe there's a this causing a that,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you will believe that there is a separate self,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you will believe that there is a separate self,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.04,0:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,separate from the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.00,0:07:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There is an it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.77,0:07:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,causing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This it should be guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.67,0:07:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thrown in hell, punished,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.67,0:07:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,rewarded, worshipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.49,0:07:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the belief in causality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.06,0:07:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,anchors the belief in a separate self
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.06,0:07:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,anchors the belief in a separate self
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.06,0:07:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and anchors the idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.06,0:07:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as an actual it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.83,0:07:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the it causing you to do all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.83,0:07:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the it causing you to do all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.83,0:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And all kinds of spiritual pathways
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.31,0:07:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are set up to destroy the it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are set up to destroy the it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.31,0:07:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanquish the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.31,0:07:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Conquer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.82,0:07:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's much easier to dissolve it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:07:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,by removing its structure
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.82,0:08:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it falls to its own accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.23,0:08:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If things are not happening
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,due to causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.23,0:08:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is no it causing a that to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.23,0:08:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then how do phenomena occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.23,0:08:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how do phenomena occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.09,0:08:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.66,0:08:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand better an analogy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.66,0:08:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.66,0:08:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.56,0:08:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity is like an infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite power
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.56,0:08:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,whose characteristic
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.59,0:08:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is more like gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Its power is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.51,0:08:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Its domain is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no beginning, no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.51,0:08:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.31,0:08:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no opinions, no feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.31,0:08:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't get angry at people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.31,0:08:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't get angry at people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.31,0:09:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not interested in vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.52,0:09:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not respectful of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,be interested in vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.77,0:09:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you're not respectful of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.61,0:09:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in for difficult times.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.92,0:09:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so if divinity is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.92,0:09:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you God.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.92,0:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If divinity is an infinite power
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's an infinite field
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.10,0:09:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll draw the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.10,0:09:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll draw God's picture this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.10,0:09:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't mind, easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So God is actually this whole
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.10,0:09:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,field here, this entire board.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.58,0:09:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a giant electromagnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're using this as a closer analogy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.58,0:09:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,than most of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.71,0:09:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of this infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.54,0:10:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful field you have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.54,0:10:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,structure, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.28,0:10:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not having technical
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.28,0:10:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,successes this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.84,0:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.20,0:10:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.45,0:10:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you have an ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It has some kind of form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.45,0:10:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got belief systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.45,0:10:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in 1927
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.45,0:10:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in Chicago, Illinois
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.45,0:10:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm son, this and this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.45,0:10:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's got definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.37,0:10:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.37,0:10:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which we call
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.37,0:10:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego structure then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.37,0:10:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is form within an infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.52,0:10:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,field of non-form.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.52,0:10:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That door of this building
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.52,0:10:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.52,0:10:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,An analogy to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.52,0:10:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Here was this big
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,giant electromagnetic crane
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.88,0:10:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out back here,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whose power is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.88,0:11:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to the scrap metal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's picking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.88,0:11:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy throws the switch,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.94,0:11:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous power picks it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.29,0:11:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to every little piece of scrap metal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,from the tiniest to the largest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.29,0:11:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is completely at the effect
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.29,0:11:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't decide
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.16,0:11:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.16,0:11:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The electromagnetic is not punishing
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this little ball bearing here,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but zap, it's pulled right into the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.56,0:11:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, over lifetimes then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.61,0:11:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what we acquire as a result
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual intention then
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.09,0:11:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,are energy fuels
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.09,0:11:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with patterns within them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.09,0:11:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which becomes our karmic destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We become like little
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.63,0:11:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,little molecules of metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.36,0:12:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a polarity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have a molecular structure
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is a composite
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,over many lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.52,0:12:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you have become now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.52,0:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is within this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.52,0:12:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.84,0:12:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that the field will
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have complete influence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.48,0:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,over the destiny of this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.48,0:12:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on how it changes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.77,0:12:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,its own polarities
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.77,0:12:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and its own opinions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,where it will go in the field then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.57,0:12:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is now up to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.57,0:12:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the content of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But the field is not going to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The field is not arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.71,0:12:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as spirit leaves the body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.71,0:12:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where it goes, obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.71,0:12:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is within the field
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.71,0:12:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where it feels comfortable
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.71,0:12:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,where it's appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.16,0:13:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Every human being
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're first born
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.26,0:13:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,already has a calibratable
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.26,0:13:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant you're born
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.32,0:13:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you can calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.32,0:13:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Every newborn infant already has
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.32,0:13:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,a calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.64,0:13:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Also,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.51,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment of birth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact moment of death
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.51,0:13:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is already defined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.51,0:13:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the means, not the how.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.51,0:13:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The exact moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.51,0:13:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have two interesting phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.88,0:13:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is born equal at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.16,0:13:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are born with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.16,0:13:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,others 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.92,0:13:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How long we'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,within a physical body is already determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.92,0:13:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if what we said is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.12,0:13:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What I've just said is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.12,0:13:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.85,0:13:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in kinesiology what we do is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,confirm things
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.85,0:14:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that are not within
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the ordinary belief system of people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.85,0:14:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet they answer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.84,0:14:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,many questions and phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.84,0:14:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people who are
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.90,0:14:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Western world are unaware
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.90,0:14:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of the whole phenomena of karma
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.03,0:14:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are busy feeling sorry for themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.03,0:14:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and resentful all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.41,0:14:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.34,0:14:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't see that everything
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is the result of an ongoing phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.34,0:14:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,over vast periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.88,0:14:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So things don't come about by
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.88,0:14:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.88,0:14:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no this causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.36,0:14:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how do phenomena occur?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thing within
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.54,0:14:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,creation then
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.60,0:14:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has its potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.18,0:14:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It has its phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.18,0:14:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and its potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.56,0:14:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And within the field of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.30,0:15:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.64,0:15:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.64,0:15:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and unfolds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.96,0:15:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you don't see is causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.96,0:15:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.96,0:15:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the ongoingness of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is continuous
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and unfolding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.80,0:15:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And to the sequential
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.80,0:15:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,perception of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.80,0:15:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.84,0:15:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sequence then demands
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.09,0:15:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,an explanation cause causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.09,0:15:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.02,0:15:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose unfolds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.63,0:15:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The rose within it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.63,0:15:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,has a karmic potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.63,0:15:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's born
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the potential
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.63,0:15:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a magnificent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.63,0:15:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,rose. But it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.69,0:15:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.69,0:15:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can force it to become
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose nor can anything cause
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:15:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it to become a rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.04,0:15:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But under appropriate conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field, under the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.27,0:16:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.30,0:16:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it then begins to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.30,0:16:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfill its potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.30,0:16:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and present itself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.30,0:16:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.30,0:16:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.42,0:16:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unfolding its potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is causing,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.42,0:16:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody here can cause
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.42,0:16:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a rose to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.24,0:16:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether a thing will manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.24,0:16:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,its potentiality depends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.24,0:16:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.16,0:16:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that karmic potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.16,0:16:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You have reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.16,0:16:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.41,0:16:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then manifesting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.79,0:16:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, creation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.95,0:16:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,are one and the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.59,0:17:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in that you see
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.61,0:17:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that evolution is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.61,0:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but the unfolding of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.64,0:17:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.73,0:17:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.73,0:17:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,between creation and evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They're identical.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.18,0:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.36,0:17:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the field
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.72,0:17:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to manifest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.84,0:17:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the potential
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.16,0:17:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.16,0:17:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.86,0:17:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,an interesting example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.99,0:17:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to suspect
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's more than
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.47,0:17:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.47,0:17:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.47,0:17:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened to one of these
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.47,0:17:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,rockets where the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.53,0:17:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,insulation fell off or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.53,0:17:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuttle deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.95,0:17:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.95,0:17:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You see they started
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.95,0:17:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.95,0:18:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn't really find
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.95,0:18:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer in causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.08,0:18:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They had some quasi examples
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.62,0:18:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but they didn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.62,0:18:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,anything definitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.62,0:18:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally they got
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw it the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it says it's the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.62,0:18:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of NASA that allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.88,0:18:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for this to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.88,0:18:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The climate. Aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.88,0:18:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They breached certain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.88,0:18:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,negligences or routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the climate. Aha.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.88,0:18:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.88,0:18:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of a climate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.88,0:18:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that war arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This person doesn't cause a war there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.88,0:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of a whole climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have a whole population.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The climate of a whole population
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.77,0:18:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to say
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.77,0:18:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,let's kill everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.77,0:18:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or let's chop up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.77,0:18:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.77,0:18:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have a climate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that can grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.35,0:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph Goebbels was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:18:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a great master of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.35,0:19:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew that it was fertile out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.35,0:19:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew how to fan the breeze
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.35,0:19:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and get everybody inflamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.41,0:19:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.76,0:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you look there
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,where is the cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.76,0:19:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well you can't have a flame
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.76,0:19:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,without tinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the tinder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,People willing to fan the flame
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.21,0:19:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see war isn't just a simple cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.50,0:19:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a net effect of a total climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.50,0:19:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.50,0:19:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the climate of course changes with the times
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the evolution of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Political sophistication,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.50,0:19:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,education
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.85,0:19:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and a thousand other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.85,0:19:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's my
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,first obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to dissuade you of the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.28,0:19:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,devotion to the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,belief system of causality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.48,0:19:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because so long as
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.40,0:19:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're reinforcing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:20:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.98,0:20:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,everything we do think and believe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.98,0:20:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is the manifestation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.98,0:20:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is like the consolidation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.98,0:20:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of a whole field
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.98,0:20:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is evolved over great
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.11,0:20:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Great periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.68,0:20:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.68,0:20:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.68,0:20:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.68,0:20:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of which I spoke last night a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.68,0:20:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How many were here last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.68,0:20:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh quite a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.75,0:20:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember I said
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there wasn't any life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,See if that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to check that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.74,0:20:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.74,0:20:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What could be called before the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.32,0:20:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.32,0:20:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.32,0:20:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the potential for life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.32,0:20:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh there was the energy of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.32,0:20:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the energy of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.64,0:20:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.98,0:21:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.98,0:21:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the energy field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was the light
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.98,0:21:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the light of energy resist
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.98,0:21:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as light resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.98,0:21:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We never asked that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.68,0:21:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.68,0:21:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we look back in history
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.68,0:21:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that life forms were extremely primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.97,0:21:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And here were these primitive life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.97,0:21:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,on a you might say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,hostile planet
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.22,0:21:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in other words it wasn't necessarily
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.22,0:21:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,friendly to life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.38,0:21:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but life began to evolve then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,by serving
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.89,0:21:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a planet with no life on it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.89,0:21:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at that time that just the beginning of life
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.89,0:21:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was merely an energy
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.89,0:21:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as yet no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.89,0:21:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And as it begins to take form then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.89,0:21:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to find a way to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.89,0:21:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first rule
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of the emergence of life then
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.89,0:21:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the biologic domain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.89,0:21:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,was survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:22:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.77,0:22:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't introduce Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.16,0:22:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because she's my right arm
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.16,0:22:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel like introducing my right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.16,0:22:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my right arm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.16,0:22:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's become my right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.19,0:22:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's like one with the work
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.19,0:22:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,one with the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're asking things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.19,0:22:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we never asked this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're always discovering
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.22,0:22:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,something new
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.22,0:22:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or a new way of looking at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.25,0:22:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So then life began
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.35,0:22:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in a very primitive form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.35,0:22:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in which its survival
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.35,0:22:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was not at all guaranteed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.35,0:22:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact quite unlikely in form
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.86,0:22:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and so life then had to be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.86,0:22:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,devoted to its own survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.86,0:22:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.89,0:22:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,life then starts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.89,0:22:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in its most primitive forms
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.89,0:22:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a germ let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.89,0:22:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's only interested
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.89,0:22:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in its own survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.34,0:22:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If we landed on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.34,0:22:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to colonize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.34,0:23:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see we would have one preoccupation
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.34,0:23:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is survival
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.34,0:23:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,getting oxygen, food, water, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.34,0:23:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So life was obsessed then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.60,0:23:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,not obsessed but
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.60,0:23:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as a matter of speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.60,0:23:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,devoted to survival
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.14,0:23:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,its survival
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.14,0:23:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.97,0:23:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The bacterium under a rock
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.97,0:23:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is not interested in the rock's survival
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.97,0:23:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's interested in its survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.71,0:23:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So life from the very beginning then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.71,0:23:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is egocentric is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.06,0:23:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.06,0:23:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the early life forms then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.06,0:23:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the bug is interested
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.06,0:23:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in eating another bug
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.06,0:23:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the primitive life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.06,0:23:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are interested in eating
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.06,0:23:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so life then
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.32,0:23:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,gets its
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.51,0:23:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,foothold by virtue
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.60,0:23:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of eating you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.60,0:23:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.56,0:23:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This becomes extremely well developed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.56,0:23:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the dinosaur
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.76,0:23:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the reptilian world
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.76,0:24:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the dinosaur is the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.49,0:24:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.49,0:24:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't care anything
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.65,0:24:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,lays an egg and walks away
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.29,0:24:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,not much maternal instinct
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.29,0:24:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,don't even hang out to see if the eggs hatch
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.29,0:24:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes off
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.29,0:24:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it's busy killing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.52,0:24:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and eating other people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.52,0:24:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,such people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.55,0:24:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,are still quite active
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.55,0:24:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.55,0:24:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in killing other people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.55,0:24:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,let's kill them
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.55,0:24:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by the thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.90,0:24:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so the reptilian
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the dinosaur
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.16,0:24:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.16,0:24:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.12,0:24:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Komodo dragon calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.12,0:24:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about 70
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so the Komodo dragon is a living example
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.12,0:24:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it is so deadly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.12,0:24:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it just bites you and walks away
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.12,0:24:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and waits till you die
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.47,0:24:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it's perfected
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.08,0:24:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,really perfected
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.84,0:25:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.27,0:25:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then we see life evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.27,0:25:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to higher forms
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.27,0:25:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't begin to see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.27,0:25:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.27,0:25:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,until you really see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.27,0:25:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the bird mother
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.68,0:25:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to pay attention to the eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.88,0:25:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,hangs around
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.88,0:25:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of the mammalian
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.88,0:25:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the maternal instinct
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.88,0:25:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the appearance of love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.88,0:25:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the consideration for something other than just my survival
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.88,0:25:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.88,0:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you see in maternal love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.88,0:25:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,risking their own survival
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.16,0:25:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for the life of the offspring
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.16,0:25:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you see the evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.16,0:25:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on up through hominid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.16,0:25:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through Neanderthal man
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.16,0:25:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates around 75
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.20,0:25:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Cro-Magnon man
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.20,0:25:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Piltdown man
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.65,0:25:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on up through the hominids
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.65,0:25:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated around 70 to 90
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.65,0:25:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.10,0:26:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the birth of Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.10,0:26:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.10,0:26:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as a whole
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.10,0:26:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,totality of mankind was 90
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.10,0:26:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,totality of mankind was 90
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.55,0:26:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.93,0:26:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.93,0:26:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time of the birth of Jesus Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.93,0:26:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was 100
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.04,0:26:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so that was the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.04,0:26:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he was speaking to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.04,0:26:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrated at 100
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.08,0:26:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,let's give some
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.08,0:26:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,depth to the field
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.08,0:26:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding his words
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.30,0:26:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then over the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.30,0:26:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12th century, 13th, 14th
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.30,0:26:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,15th, 16th, 17th
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.30,0:26:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if you calibrate all the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.30,0:26:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you find it calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.30,0:26:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,level 190
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.30,0:26:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,1600s, 1700s, 1800s
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.30,0:26:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,1900s
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.30,0:26:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the time I was born 190
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.30,0:26:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.57,0:26:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.34,0:26:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirit of truth doesn't start
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.34,0:27:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,till calibrated level 200
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.34,0:27:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.44,0:27:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.98,0:27:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.98,0:27:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it was devoted to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.98,0:27:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.17,0:27:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.17,0:27:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,makes sense
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.17,0:27:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you say well throughout the ages
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.17,0:27:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.17,0:27:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,during the dark ages was 190
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.17,0:27:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.36,0:27:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the inquisition and all those things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.36,0:27:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,don't seem quite as despicable
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.36,0:27:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the reading
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.36,0:27:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the vikings
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.36,0:27:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the great hordes of the savages
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.36,0:27:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in the lombards
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.36,0:27:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and Genghis Khan and all
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.81,0:27:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,at 190
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.45,0:27:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the way consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.45,0:27:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,perceives survival
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.45,0:27:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is we have to kill you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.61,0:27:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.60,0:27:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then in the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.60,0:27:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness level jumped to over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.60,0:27:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to 207
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.60,0:27:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,where it exists till this day
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.83,0:28:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which means mankind now has a new
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.83,0:28:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,future
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.18,0:28:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,has new standards of conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.40,0:28:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the field of 207 then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.40,0:28:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,contextualizes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.67,0:28:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,life in a completely different way
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.67,0:28:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,than does consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.67,0:28:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,level 190
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.02,0:28:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 190
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.02,0:28:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in which I grew up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.05,0:28:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with success
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.50,0:28:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you went to college to be a success
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.50,0:28:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,your parents said I hope you'll be a success
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.50,0:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you were supposed to be a success
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.56,0:28:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you were supposed to stay
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.57,0:28:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as principled as you could
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.64,0:28:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but when it comes to giant corporations
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.64,0:28:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to bend that little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.64,0:28:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to influence the stock price
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.86,0:28:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can do your stock options
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.86,0:28:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.86,0:28:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,heads began to roll
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.86,0:28:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so after it went to 205 then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.44,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or 207
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:28:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is today
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.66,0:29:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where is consciousness level today
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.66,0:29:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.30,0:29:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.30,0:29:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.30,0:29:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is still at 207 resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.30,0:29:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,went to 208
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.30,0:29:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,well not yet
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.36,0:29:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,pray harder folks
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.36,0:29:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,207
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.36,0:29:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the vast amount of time
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.55,0:29:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,over which consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.55,0:29:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then manifests as life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.55,0:29:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and then life evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.55,0:29:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it isn't until
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.71,0:29:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.71,0:29:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that it even gets over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.71,0:29:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.19,0:29:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,first level of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.83,0:29:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,on the calibrated scale of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.83,0:29:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that calibrates under 200
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.83,0:29:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.83,0:29:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,anything over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.83,0:29:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which is truth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.43,0:29:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go strong
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.43,0:29:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,until the late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.52,0:29:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.52,0:30:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.64,0:30:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,made you go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.64,0:30:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so in a way that sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.05,0:30:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualizes history
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.15,0:30:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.15,0:30:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.15,0:30:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of criticizing and faulting
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.15,0:30:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and putting down
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.15,0:30:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened in the past
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.47,0:30:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you were doing what they thought
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.47,0:30:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,was ethical
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.47,0:30:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you were supposed to get ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.47,0:30:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and be successful
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.47,0:30:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore that was
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.98,0:30:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the great world of materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.98,0:30:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,materialism
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.98,0:30:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,success, possessions, cars, address
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.98,0:30:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,how much money you were worth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.02,0:30:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,now the calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.02,0:30:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has reached 207
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.02,0:30:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,now you see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.02,0:30:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the level of integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.08,0:30:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so we see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.08,0:30:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity then
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.08,0:30:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the beginning of empowerment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.08,0:30:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,before that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.37,0:30:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you see inflation and pride
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.37,0:30:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,so at 190
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.37,0:31:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the world was coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.37,0:31:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of prideful indifference
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.37,0:31:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to the rights of others
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.63,0:31:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.88,0:31:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when the Germans lost the war
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.88,0:31:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler said
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.88,0:31:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they didn't deserve to live
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.01,0:31:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and he ordered that Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.01,0:31:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,should be destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.01,0:31:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Paris should be burned down
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.01,0:31:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the Eiffel Tower should be burned down
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.40,0:31:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you say that in that kind of a field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.40,0:31:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to us it would sound like insanity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.40,0:31:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because the field here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.40,0:31:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably 435 or so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.40,0:31:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so at 435
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.40,0:31:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that sounds like insanity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.40,0:31:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with the masses
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.40,0:31:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who are living down below
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.40,0:31:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.40,0:31:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if the masses of humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.40,0:31:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,are living down here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.40,0:31:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,how easy it is to control them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.43,0:31:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,with falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.43,0:31:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because their consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.43,0:31:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is dominated by falsehood
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.43,0:31:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,grief, apathy, threat
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.43,0:31:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can appeal to their desires
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.81,0:31:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so it was the world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.81,0:32:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.81,0:32:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,we grew up in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.81,0:32:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.81,0:32:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were angry
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.81,0:32:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and they got our way
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.99,0:32:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were prideful of our accomplishments
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.99,0:32:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so it was a different world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.44,0:32:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,than what we live in today
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.44,0:32:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have a new paradigm of virtue
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.44,0:32:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is as I spoke of last night
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.44,0:32:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.44,0:32:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.44,0:32:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to spill the milk
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.56,0:32:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll take care of it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.56,0:32:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,get my check tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.80,0:32:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just wanted to first address
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.80,0:32:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the totality of the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.80,0:32:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.80,0:32:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which is slowly evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.80,0:32:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.80,0:32:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,take us beyond the polarity of good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.80,0:32:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.05,0:32:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,what should we say
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.05,0:33:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all the bacteria are evil
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.05,0:33:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are only interested in themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.37,0:33:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if you superimpose
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.50,0:33:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on this phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.50,0:33:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.14,0:33:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a moralistic code
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.75,0:33:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see how ridiculous it looks
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.75,0:33:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet that's what mankind has done
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.75,0:33:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and traditional religion in a way
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.75,0:33:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has done, reinforced
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.02,0:33:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,if we see that it is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.24,0:33:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,critical for the establishment of life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.24,0:33:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to be self-interested
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.24,0:33:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,then you see how the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.37,0:33:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,became so powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.06,0:33:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego became in its own view
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.06,0:33:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of survival
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.06,0:33:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and mankind to a degree
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.51,0:33:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,worshipped the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.51,0:33:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,when it didn't worship the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.51,0:33:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he took its basic characteristics
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.67,0:33:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and projected them
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.67,0:33:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,anthropomorphically onto a god
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.67,0:33:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that was exactly like the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.73,0:33:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,angry, jealous, spitful
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.73,0:34:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,punitive
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.52,0:34:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,judgmental
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.52,0:34:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all you're talking about is the human ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.52,0:34:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the human ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.58,0:34:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to call it god
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.58,0:34:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with an E
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.58,0:34:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the capital E for God's ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.58,0:34:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and a small E for man's ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.58,0:34:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity would have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.96,0:34:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,something devoid of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.96,0:34:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the characteristics of form
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.96,0:34:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.19,0:34:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what we call the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.19,0:34:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, so
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.28,0:34:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't usually start
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.40,0:34:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the lectures with that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.40,0:34:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but we did it today
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.66,0:34:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the way it happened
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.66,0:34:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.62,0:34:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's everybody's fault here
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.32,0:34:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you made me do it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.41,0:34:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, so now you have
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.41,0:34:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,a more benign view of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.41,0:34:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not an evil it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.41,0:34:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to battle
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.41,0:34:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and struggle against
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.41,0:35:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel guilty about
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.41,0:35:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to wallow in guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.41,0:35:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and penance
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.41,0:35:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and self-flagellation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.01,0:35:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,psychically or physically
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.01,0:35:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that the structure of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.46,0:35:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is primarily animal
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.46,0:35:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's interested in that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.46,0:35:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which an animal is interested in
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.46,0:35:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,survival, serving oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and progresses
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.07,0:35:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.48,0:35:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,pack formation
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.48,0:35:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,loyalty
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.48,0:35:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the animal behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.48,0:35:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in competition for mates
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.48,0:35:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for territory
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.92,0:35:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,territoriality
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.92,0:35:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you see aggression in all of its forms
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.36,0:35:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and so that's really the basic structure
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.71,0:35:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.19,0:35:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually just an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.19,0:35:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,alright, then as man learned to think
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.19,0:35:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then he
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.19,0:36:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,see man still has the animal structures
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.22,0:36:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but then along came the frontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.22,0:36:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he could think
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.83,0:36:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,so what did man do?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.83,0:36:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,he still stayed an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.99,0:36:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he's a thinking animal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.99,0:36:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he used to do it with teeth and claws
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.50,0:36:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,now he does it with bombs and tanks
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.50,0:36:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing has changed
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.56,0:36:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,now his intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.59,0:36:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he seeks to dominate other tribes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.59,0:36:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with his intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.10,0:36:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the democrats and the liberals
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.10,0:36:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these people
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.10,0:36:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are just an animal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.36,0:36:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a talking animal
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.36,0:36:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he did what it had fur
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.60,0:36:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I want your territory
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.60,0:36:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I want power over you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.60,0:36:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to follow me
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.60,0:36:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to join my pack
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.86,0:36:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and like monkey island
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.86,0:36:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,they divide in
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.86,0:36:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they throw you know what at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.86,0:36:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in monkey island
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.86,0:36:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,typical political discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.86,0:37:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.11,0:37:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said last night
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.46,0:37:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as spiritual people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.46,0:37:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,how can we accept
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.46,0:37:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what is and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.07,0:37:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because once you see that the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.07,0:37:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is nothing but a manifestation of animal nature
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.07,0:37:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the intellect is merely an expansion of that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.07,0:37:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get off good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.07,0:37:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get off good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.07,0:37:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's one of the most difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.07,0:37:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of all polarities to get off of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.58,0:37:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably don't get off that duality
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.58,0:37:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,until about consciousness level 850
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.58,0:37:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.58,0:37:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you transcend good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.58,0:37:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're over 800
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.58,0:37:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,825, 840
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.58,0:37:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,850, 855
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.58,0:37:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,860
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.38,0:37:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so it's a very difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.17,0:37:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,polarity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.17,0:37:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,duality of the opposites
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.17,0:37:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin to dissolve
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.44,0:37:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the demonization
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.44,0:37:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which we call evil
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.86,0:37:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.53,0:38:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see it then
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.53,0:38:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from a more forgiving and accepting
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.53,0:38:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoint without having to demonize
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.53,0:38:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it and vilify it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.53,0:38:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you demonize it and vilify it out there
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.53,0:38:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you will do it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.53,0:38:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.88,0:38:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you will do it against yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.36,0:38:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,those who do the course of miracles
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.26,0:38:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,know that forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.26,0:38:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ultimate answer to just about 99%
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.26,0:38:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of every problem humans have
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.26,0:38:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and the question is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.45,0:38:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you forgive something
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.45,0:38:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that looks dead evil
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.84,0:38:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,says the Holy Spirit will
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.87,0:38:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualize it for us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.87,0:38:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that's my languaging for what the Holy Spirit does
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.87,0:38:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualizes it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.87,0:38:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so this morning what we've tried to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.87,0:38:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,recontextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.87,0:38:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the evolution of consciousness then
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.87,0:38:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can witness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.87,0:38:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that which we consider to be spiritually unfavorable
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.87,0:38:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,not as evil
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.87,0:38:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not as horrible
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.03,0:38:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not as something to beat ourselves about
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.03,0:39:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or other people about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.06,0:39:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but a natural consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.06,0:39:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.06,0:39:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as it came up through
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.06,0:39:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and developed into form
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.06,0:39:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,higher and higher form
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.06,0:39:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,began to express itself in the human
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.06,0:39:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.69,0:39:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then it expanded its animal nature
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.69,0:39:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and really used the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.69,0:39:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as another tool of its animal nature
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.69,0:39:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.24,0:39:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,become man
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.72,0:39:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in its true meaning with a capital M
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.72,0:39:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,until you begin to see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.72,0:39:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind has other uses
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.72,0:39:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,other than subserving animal instincts
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.72,0:39:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,subserving animal instincts
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.55,0:39:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and a group
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.80,0:39:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,like this has discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.80,0:39:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.80,0:39:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because here you've got
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.80,0:39:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.80,0:39:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced in the 400's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.80,0:39:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.80,0:39:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the use of the intellect
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.80,0:39:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is to discover spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.86,0:39:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ways to God
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.86,0:40:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has other uses
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.86,0:40:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,other than killing other people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.86,0:40:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for profit or fun
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.86,0:40:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for fun
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.86,0:40:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.37,0:40:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go back to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.91,0:40:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't talk about slide one yet
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.35,0:40:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked about slide one
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.35,0:40:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is applied
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.35,0:40:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but we didn't talk about it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.44,0:40:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a more abstract viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.70,0:40:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the development of the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.70,0:40:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.70,0:40:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted as a consequence of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.70,0:40:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,rather profound inner experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.70,0:40:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that went on in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.70,0:40:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning in this life at age three
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.70,0:40:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and becoming more
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.70,0:40:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,profound in teenage
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.70,0:40:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually through life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.70,0:40:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.24,0:40:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.24,0:40:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.24,0:40:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I just merely understood it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.24,0:40:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from a different viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.24,0:40:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps other people had
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.33,0:41:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,they saw it as a local phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.33,0:41:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you put the fig over your
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.33,0:41:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,stomach and if your arm goes weak
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.33,0:41:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're allergic to figs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.33,0:41:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,was sort of a very primitive
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.33,0:41:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,first application of it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.43,0:41:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so it saw it as a local phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.43,0:41:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried to give a local
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.43,0:41:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.84,0:41:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when I saw it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.84,0:41:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw wow
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.84,0:41:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this is connection between mind and body
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.84,0:41:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.88,0:41:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what is answering the question is not
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.88,0:41:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the body at all
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.88,0:41:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.88,0:41:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the body doesn't know anything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.88,0:41:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there are books that tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.94,0:41:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,your body knows everything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.94,0:41:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I got news for you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.94,0:41:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,your body doesn't know anything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.94,0:41:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a complete idiot
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.44,0:41:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ask my body anything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.44,0:41:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a stupid thing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.44,0:41:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what did I have for breakfast this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.70,0:41:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.92,0:41:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't know what I had for breakfast this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.90,0:41:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,don't look to the body for salvation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.90,0:42:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's there for fun
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.57,0:42:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.57,0:42:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a pet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.57,0:42:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I discovered my body as a pet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because after I came out of a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.57,0:42:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,state in which
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.57,0:42:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind became silent and still
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.70,0:42:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is still silent and still
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.08,0:42:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if I listen to it now
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.08,0:42:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hear anything
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.08,0:42:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't say anything
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.66,0:42:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't think anything
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.66,0:42:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it came into that state
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.81,0:42:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and here is this body walking around
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.81,0:42:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed to do fine by itself in space
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.97,0:42:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nobody running it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.97,0:42:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no you running it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.97,0:42:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's running itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.97,0:42:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't need you at all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.97,0:42:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you see what it does by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.97,0:42:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't need me at all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.60,0:42:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,see what it does by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.60,0:42:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it does it by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.60,0:42:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I never know what it's going to do until it does it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.45,0:43:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wow
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.51,0:43:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,actually the body is a nuisance
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.99,0:43:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to me it's a nuisance
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.99,0:43:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,why people price it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.99,0:43:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always in your way
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.99,0:43:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what you want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.99,0:43:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,your body is in the way to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.99,0:43:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to keep it there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.92,0:43:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to park it someplace
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.92,0:43:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,think what it costs you to keep this thing going
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.92,0:43:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.40,0:43:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be happy goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.40,0:43:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to drag it around every place
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.40,0:43:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like luggage or something
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.40,0:43:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so what I saw was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.23,0:43:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness was
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.23,0:43:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,responding just as you saw
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.23,0:43:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with Susan this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.00,0:43:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer then
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.00,0:43:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is that consciousness recognizes reality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.00,0:43:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,anything that calibrates over time
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.00,0:43:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.37,0:43:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then makes you go strong
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.08,0:43:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is below 200
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.08,0:43:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,which is fallacious
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.08,0:44:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which has no truth
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.30,0:44:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not right and wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.00,0:44:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or yes and no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.00,0:44:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the kinesiologic response is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.06,0:44:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,yes and not yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.06,0:44:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,nature cannot answer with a no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.22,0:44:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it can answer with a yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.73,0:44:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or it doesn't answer at all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.73,0:44:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so when our arm goes weak
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.73,0:44:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not a no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.08,0:44:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a not yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.24,0:44:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a slide here
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.24,0:44:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if we'll get to it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.24,0:44:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.24,0:44:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,connecting quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.40,0:44:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with kinesiology and consciousness research
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.40,0:44:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but in line with quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.16,0:44:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the theory of quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.16,0:44:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the universe can only answer yes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.22,0:44:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it cannot answer with no
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.38,0:44:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,through the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.38,0:44:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can collapse the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.38,0:44:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,through consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.38,0:44:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's how we as spiritual people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.38,0:44:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,influence the collective consciousness of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.38,0:44:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as each one of us makes a positive
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.38,0:44:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we can collapse the wave function
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.38,0:45:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of potentiality into actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.38,0:45:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually change the field
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.38,0:45:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we actually have an influence on the field
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.38,0:45:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.96,0:45:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,praying quietly
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.96,0:45:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,every forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.96,0:45:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,every act of kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.05,0:45:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,every time you see a little beetle
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.05,0:45:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to just turn him over
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.05,0:45:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can get on his way
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.05,0:45:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and give him a twig
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.05,0:45:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so he gets a foothold again
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.05,0:45:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that changes the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.40,0:45:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,every act of kindness is noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.60,0:45:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's true
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.60,0:45:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,scripture says every hair of your head
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.60,0:45:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,shall be counted
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.60,0:45:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that's an absolute fact
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.60,0:45:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,every hair of your head
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.60,0:45:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is known and counted
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.60,0:45:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,not only is it known and counted
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.60,0:45:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's knowable and countable forever
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.60,0:45:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,within the field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.17,0:45:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,every single thought
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.17,0:45:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling, decision, action
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.20,0:45:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is registered forever
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.20,0:45:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of time and space
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.20,0:45:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is beyond form
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.30,0:45:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and time and space
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.30,0:46:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it is indestructible
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.80,0:46:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you destroy that which has no form
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.80,0:46:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing has to have form
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.80,0:46:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to destroy it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.06,0:46:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so that means that everything that ever happened
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.06,0:46:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.06,0:46:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is retrievable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.06,0:46:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.35,0:46:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in one instant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.53,0:46:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what Napoleon thought or felt
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.53,0:46:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,when he walked in the pyramid
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.53,0:46:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what he thought and felt
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.91,0:46:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when he walked out of the pyramid
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.91,0:46:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,how he felt about whoever his girlfriend was at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.91,0:46:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what they had for breakfast
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.96,0:46:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we used to check on Saddam what he had for breakfast
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.96,0:46:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when we did these
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.96,0:46:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we used to check what he had for breakfast that morning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.96,0:46:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is knowable
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.96,0:46:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is knowable within an instant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.09,0:46:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the only requirement is that the people
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.09,0:46:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,asking the question are doing so
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.09,0:46:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,from a position of integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.09,0:46:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,they themselves have to calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.09,0:46:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.32,0:46:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the question itself has to be integrous
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.32,0:47:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that means your devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.32,0:47:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is to the truth and not to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.32,0:47:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,finding some agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.38,0:47:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to ask me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.00,0:47:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what about President Bush
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.00,0:47:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there's also some idiot in the back
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.12,0:47:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what about Saddam Hussein
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.12,0:47:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you're looking to reinforce
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.76,0:47:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a belief system
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.76,0:47:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got your own ideas of good and evil
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.76,0:47:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you want to use it to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.76,0:47:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,prove what you already believe
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.76,0:47:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not the way you do science
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.76,0:47:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you do science with no presumptions
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.76,0:47:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.99,0:47:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you're devoted to the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.99,0:47:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because the pathway to God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.08,0:47:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is through
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.08,0:47:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.71,0:47:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,devotional non-duality means then
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.71,0:47:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to go beyond the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.71,0:47:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.93,0:47:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and one's devotion is to truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.93,0:48:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so if the intention
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.35,0:48:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of asking a question then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.35,0:48:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is to discern what is the absolute truth
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.35,0:48:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then the results
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.48,0:48:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are relatively accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.96,0:48:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the test is done quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.96,0:48:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a very fast test
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.96,0:48:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer only lasts a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.96,0:48:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you delay you won't get a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.96,0:48:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,good result
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.96,0:48:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,what you'll get is what I call
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.05,0:48:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the falling out of the tree recovery
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.05,0:48:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because the arm when it falls
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.05,0:48:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in the primitive ape in you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.05,0:48:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,think it's falling out of a tree
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.37,0:48:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it begins to try to right itself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.37,0:48:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so you have to catch the response quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.92,0:48:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise the body will
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.92,0:48:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say a flash of weakness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.92,0:48:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it will begin to resist that weakness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.92,0:48:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it wants to hang into the tree
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.92,0:48:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and not follow the tree
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.92,0:48:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so the trick is done very very quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.92,0:48:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,people ask us about it
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.92,0:48:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the technique we're telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.92,0:48:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you use very little pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.92,0:48:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you use very little pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.92,0:48:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,two fingers and you press down
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.92,0:48:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say resist
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.95,0:48:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I'm not using a lot of pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.95,0:49:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's not pushing back
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.95,0:49:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,with a lot of pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.95,0:49:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do it delicately
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.95,0:49:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so because I compare it with other things
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.95,0:49:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.95,0:49:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so if I say a bear is a friendly animal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.95,0:49:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,resist
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.01,0:49:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,see it's a very quick response
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.17,0:49:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,a bear is not a friendly animal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.17,0:49:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he can be taught to be semi-friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.17,0:49:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he can be taught to be semi-friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.17,0:49:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,not really friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.33,0:49:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he's good because he gets rewarded for being good
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.26,0:49:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's not really friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.26,0:49:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but he's not really friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.26,0:49:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said last night
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.26,0:49:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in a spiritual despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.26,0:49:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in a spiritual despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.26,0:49:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got two little friends in the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.26,0:49:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,ready to rescue you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.26,0:49:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one is to know that a kitty's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.42,0:49:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.42,0:49:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that a dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.42,0:49:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.42,0:49:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so those are two things I said last night
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.42,0:49:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanted to repeat them again today
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.42,0:49:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how can it be that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.64,0:49:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,through the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.64,0:50:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that a kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.25,0:50:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a kitty's purr is 500
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.25,0:50:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where's our
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.25,0:50:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody keeps taking that off on us
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.25,0:50:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,every time we try that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.79,0:50:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a kitty's purr is 500
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.79,0:50:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.79,0:50:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.79,0:50:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a kitty's purr is 500
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.88,0:50:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.88,0:50:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog's wagging tail is 500
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.88,0:50:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a dog that just loves everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.88,0:50:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes friends with everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.88,0:50:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who comes to the house
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.88,0:50:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,has to greet everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.06,0:50:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so instead of some long gone
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.06,0:50:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the statue of some long gone saint
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.06,0:50:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're not feeling too good spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.06,0:50:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better to picture
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.06,0:50:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a purring kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.06,0:50:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,get into the kitty's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.06,0:50:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because there you've got unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.06,0:50:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in the dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.25,0:50:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so how is it that these two animals
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.25,0:50:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,bypass
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.34,0:50:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,something like 90% of humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.34,0:50:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,90% of humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.34,0:51:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,never gets to be a purring kitty
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.34,0:51:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or a wagging dog tail
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.34,0:51:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.73,0:51:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,why that happened
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.73,0:51:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.73,0:51:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so on the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.73,0:51:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then what we discovered was
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.73,0:51:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget how we started doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.60,0:51:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we used kinesiology then
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.60,0:51:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we started using it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.60,0:51:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in abstract questions
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.60,0:51:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and things throughout time and space
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.60,0:51:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we did all the Greek atheism
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.76,0:51:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we did cathedrals
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.76,0:51:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we did countries
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.76,0:51:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,writers, authors
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.98,0:51:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,movies we've calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.98,0:51:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,just about everything on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.98,0:51:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,current book we've done 3000 calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.98,0:51:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're only half way through
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.08,0:51:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,if she holds up
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.08,0:51:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll finish the book
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.04,0:51:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,well we do a run
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.04,0:51:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,when she's in the mood
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.04,0:51:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then she'll say I can't do anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.04,0:52:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we did 100 movies I can't do anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.07,0:52:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.40,0:52:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we found that then you could calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.40,0:52:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the classical levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.40,0:52:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,which have been traditional throughout the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.40,0:52:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.88,0:52:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got the very lowest
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.88,0:52:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,shame and guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.98,0:52:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy, grief
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.08,0:52:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then it comes up to fear
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.08,0:52:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then desire, greed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.59,0:52:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,anger, rage, hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.59,0:52:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,pride, courage
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.45,0:52:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,these make you go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.45,0:52:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the domain of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.45,0:52:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this is where most people on the planet live
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.45,0:52:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,most of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.93,0:52:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and from a spiritual viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.30,0:52:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,traditionally these have been condemned
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.30,0:52:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not only do you have this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.91,0:52:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but you feel guilty about it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.91,0:52:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in case you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.04,0:52:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the nearest church will inform you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.04,0:52:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you should be doing penance
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.96,0:53:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there's another way of looking at it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.16,0:53:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the way to God is through joy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.16,0:53:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.16,0:53:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and through truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.16,0:53:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not through self condemnation
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.16,0:53:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,anger, self pity
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.25,0:53:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,resentment and guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.25,0:53:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,crawling on your knees from here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.28,0:53:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to the nearest cathedral
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.54,0:53:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,may be impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.39,0:53:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it will make you enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.83,0:53:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,another way of viewing these things
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.83,0:53:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from a positive viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.83,0:53:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is each one of these is an improvement
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.83,0:53:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,over that which is below it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.12,0:53:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.28,0:53:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in the office they bring in a patient
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.28,0:53:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done psychiatry for 50 years
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.28,0:53:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they bring in an old lady
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.28,0:53:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who sits there and rocks and won't eat
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.28,0:53:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,looks off into space
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.47,0:53:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,take this pill mother
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.69,0:53:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it will make you feel better
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.69,0:53:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,she just rocks and looks off into space
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.76,0:53:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,way down here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.76,0:53:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,way down here
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.92,0:53:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.10,0:54:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,apathetic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.52,0:54:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as we'll see later
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.52,0:54:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,if we ever get to the slides
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.64,0:54:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,whole continents live here
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.71,0:54:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,continents
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.71,0:54:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not just individual people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.84,0:54:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll show you continents
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.84,0:54:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrate at 60
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.84,0:54:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,whole continents
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.84,0:54:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where the entire population
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.84,0:54:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this is where they calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.84,0:54:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,not enough energy to feed themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.70,0:54:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,not enough energy to control their
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.70,0:54:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,own behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.70,0:54:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,dying right and left of AIDS
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.70,0:54:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and disease
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.83,0:54:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.83,0:54:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and malnutrition
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.83,0:54:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and infection
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.83,0:54:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and if they manage to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.83,0:54:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a neighboring tribe will slaughter them anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.92,0:54:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,average age of death 12 and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.92,0:54:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,average age of death in those countries
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.92,0:54:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,12 and a half
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.12,0:54:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the survival very slim
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.12,0:54:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,now
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.04,0:54:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.04,0:54:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that we say fear is awful
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.04,0:55:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.04,0:55:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,if you had the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.04,0:55:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,enough energy to be fearful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.04,0:55:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you could do something about the apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.08,0:55:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you can run like hell
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.08,0:55:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in fear right
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.08,0:55:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in fear you can build buildings
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.11,0:55:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,fortresses
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.11,0:55:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're scared of starving to death
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.11,0:55:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's amazing what you can do
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.17,0:55:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just with your fingers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.40,0:55:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's bad viewed from here
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.40,0:55:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but viewed from here
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.40,0:55:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a great improvement
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.43,0:55:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a major jump is to desire
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.43,0:55:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when you get people out of apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.43,0:55:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so the benefit of television
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.43,0:55:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world is that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.43,0:55:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,cultures that live down here in apathy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.43,0:55:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,look on television
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.43,0:55:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.43,0:55:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa look how those people live
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.43,0:55:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to want something
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.43,0:55:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so for them to awaken the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.43,0:55:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is a major improvement
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.43,0:55:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,these people are down here
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.46,0:55:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.46,0:55:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.46,0:55:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,it's true
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.49,0:55:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in a nursing home
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.49,0:56:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't have the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.81,0:56:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to go to the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.81,0:56:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you can get them up to fear
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.84,0:56:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.84,0:56:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fear of overpopulation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.32,0:56:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,overpopulation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.32,0:56:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,will drive you into starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.36,0:56:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to desire
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.36,0:56:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher level of living
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.71,0:56:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you get angry
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.71,0:56:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't have it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.16,0:56:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,anger then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.22,0:56:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,has a lot of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.22,0:56:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you can do a lot out of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.22,0:56:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and a lot out of desire
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.22,0:56:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then pride
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.57,0:56:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,feeds more energy back into it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.99,0:56:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so you enlist people into the Marines
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.99,0:56:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,based on pride
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.02,0:56:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but the Marines
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.31,0:56:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want you to hang out in pride
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.31,0:56:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because people in pride
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.31,0:56:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,are a pain in the neck
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.50,0:56:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to get them up to courage
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.50,0:56:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,pride gets you into service
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.50,0:56:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but courage is what it takes to face the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.50,0:56:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.50,0:56:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you finally have launched over
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.50,0:56:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,first step in the 12 step program
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.50,0:57:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.50,0:57:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.50,0:57:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.01,0:57:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that without God's help
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.01,0:57:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unlikely that my consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.56,0:57:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.56,0:57:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,much less become enlightened
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.56,0:57:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,without God's help
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.56,0:57:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm helpless without God's help
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.75,0:57:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see weakness then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.75,0:57:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.75,0:57:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.75,0:57:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and power comes from the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.75,0:57:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and when this says
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.75,0:57:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I am myself and I'm unable to accomplish this
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.75,0:57:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I must turn to the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.75,0:57:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,well the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.75,0:57:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.77,0:57:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing the power of the field can't do
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.77,0:57:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so as we surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.19,0:57:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our will to God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.28,0:57:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask God to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.28,0:57:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we ask to understand God's will for us
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.76,0:57:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,now we're invoking
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.76,0:57:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.76,0:57:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego within itself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.92,0:57:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is looking to its ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.92,0:57:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and other egos
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.92,0:58:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,vote for me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.92,0:58:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,buy my product
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.08,0:58:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,fear my gun
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.37,0:58:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.37,0:58:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,now we're invoking
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.37,0:58:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.37,0:58:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so as you begin to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.24,0:58:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.24,0:58:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when you fall overboard
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.24,0:58:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.24,0:58:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you give all this up
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.24,0:58:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and you surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.62,0:58:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly you find that you can float
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.62,0:58:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the navy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.62,0:58:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and a minesweeper
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.62,0:58:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I got swept off
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.84,0:58:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I had to do was float
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.84,0:58:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.84,0:58:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the Huangpu river of all places in Shanghai
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.84,0:58:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with dead bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.97,0:58:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and God knows what else in the water
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.97,0:58:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to not think about that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.97,0:58:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.97,0:58:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I floated along and what do you know
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.97,0:58:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,here was a warship
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.97,0:58:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they were docked side by side
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.97,0:58:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm carrying down this strong current
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.97,0:58:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and here's the prow of a warship right ahead of me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.97,0:58:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm headed right for this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.97,0:59:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just went like this against the prow
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.97,0:59:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the water kept me there
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.97,0:59:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they came and got me
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.97,0:59:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so you see the power of the field saved my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.97,0:59:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if I kept struggling I would have killed myself
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.23,0:59:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.23,0:59:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so our survival then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.23,0:59:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is up to the field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.23,0:59:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so the ego claims credit
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.23,0:59:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for our survival
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.23,0:59:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but the power of our survival
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.23,0:59:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is within the field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.23,0:59:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the field that decides
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.23,0:59:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to pull the chocks out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.23,0:59:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when the moment of physical death
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.23,0:59:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,arises
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.28,0:59:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's a lot of good news this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.28,0:59:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,one is that the moment of your death
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.28,0:59:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is already set
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.28,0:59:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can forget worrying about it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.28,0:59:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to worry whether asparagus
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.28,0:59:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to shorten your life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.28,0:59:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it's not going to shorten your life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.28,0:59:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's death by a scary asparagus
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.28,0:59:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.28,0:59:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody is so fearful in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.34,0:59:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.34,0:59:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,science in the public interest
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.34,0:59:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is something I was telling you
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.34,1:00:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,some new horror story
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.20,1:00:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when you get out of the car
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.20,1:00:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a higher case of being killed in an accident
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.20,1:00:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so everybody moves to the left rear
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.20,1:00:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,being on the highway in the first place
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.20,1:00:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is a risk factor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.20,1:00:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so why are you driving if you're so scared of everything
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.20,1:00:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to eat this
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.20,1:00:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with kernels on it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.20,1:00:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you get blocked in by all these fears
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.20,1:00:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.20,1:00:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ego is telling you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.20,1:00:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to save you boy
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.20,1:00:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.20,1:00:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in the end it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.20,1:00:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the other good news
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.27,1:00:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it's not possible
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.27,1:00:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience your own physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.27,1:00:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that is not a possibility
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.39,1:00:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,those of you who have died
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.39,1:00:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to come back in the body
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.39,1:00:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are aware of that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.22,1:00:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people have had near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.22,1:00:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not so many here
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.32,1:00:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.32,1:00:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,those who had near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.32,1:00:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,those who calibrated over 600
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.32,1:00:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and remember past lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.32,1:01:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,remember that in one instant you're in the body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.32,1:01:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,next minute you're out and you're looking at it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.50,1:01:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and there it is laying there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.50,1:01:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't experience your own physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.95,1:01:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so I just thought
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.46,1:01:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that might be helpful
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.46,1:01:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because so many people are afraid of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.46,1:01:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.49,1:01:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't experience it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.49,1:01:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody can experience physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.49,1:01:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because the you is no longer there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.49,1:01:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it's not there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.49,1:01:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,how can they experience what's there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.49,1:01:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.49,1:01:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people here have gone out of body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.49,1:01:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,out of body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.49,1:01:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,more out of bodies than near deathers
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.49,1:01:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,ok
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.49,1:01:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,well you know the instant you're out of body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.49,1:01:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the you is up here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.49,1:01:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and the body is down there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.49,1:01:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but that which is me
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.49,1:01:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is up here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.49,1:01:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the me is up here
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.49,1:01:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of self
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.04,1:01:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,me, I
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.20,1:01:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the focus of your existence
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.20,1:01:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,has nothing to do with the physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.20,1:01:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because the physicality is laying down there
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.20,1:02:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.61,1:02:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the beginning of spiritual truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.61,1:02:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 200
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.61,1:02:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the arm goes strong
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.61,1:02:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,one is empowered by truth
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.61,1:02:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.64,1:02:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you go to neutrality
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.64,1:02:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,courage is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.64,1:02:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you still can feel fear
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.64,1:02:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in courage
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.64,1:02:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you can still feel fear
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.64,1:02:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but walk into the bullets anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.64,1:02:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and many a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.64,1:02:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is often gone through
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.64,1:02:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,before one is finally
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.64,1:02:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for a higher principle, a higher cause
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.64,1:02:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to face the bullets
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.12,1:02:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually die for the cause
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.12,1:02:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they have conquered all of this
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.12,1:02:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.18,1:02:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is a more comfortable level called neutral
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.18,1:02:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.18,1:02:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it's ok if you get the job
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.18,1:02:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's ok if you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.82,1:02:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness is an even higher energy level
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.82,1:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,neutral she serves you your breakfast
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.82,1:02:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,she takes your order in the restaurant
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.82,1:02:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but she doesn't really look you in the eye
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.01,1:03:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness is how can I help you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.01,1:03:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're getting closer and closer to Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.01,1:03:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as we get up there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.01,1:03:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.33,1:03:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.49,1:03:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,laughter
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.52,1:03:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we did all the corporations in America
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.52,1:03:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.52,1:03:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I know there's Walmart haters out there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.52,1:03:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll have to forgive me
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.52,1:03:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.52,1:03:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,whether people like it or not Walmart calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.52,1:03:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than any corporation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.52,1:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it is also the largest corporation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.52,1:03:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it also has the biggest bottom line
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.52,1:03:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so what's strange about Walmart
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.52,1:03:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is that they
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.52,1:03:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to be friendly
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.52,1:03:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I help you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.52,1:03:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't like the product bring it back
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.52,1:03:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we give you your money
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.52,1:03:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so he bought the product
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.52,1:03:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on sale
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.88,1:03:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you were thinking it'd I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.88,1:03:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the videos
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.88,1:03:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.88,1:03:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.16,1:03:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,good
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.16,1:03:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,some people
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.16,1:03:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.16,1:04:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,well
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.16,1:04:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.16,1:04:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,them
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.16,1:04:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,make money
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.16,1:04:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.16,1:04:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Calvary's higher than any corporation in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.96,1:04:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's interesting, that spiritual principles,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.74,1:04:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're applied to everyday life, are not airy-fairy.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.28,1:04:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual principles of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.18,1:04:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,are the most profoundly important thing in business.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.75,1:04:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's integrity that shows up on the bottom line.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.20,1:04:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got the example of Walmart.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.32,1:04:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart's the biggest corporation in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.20,1:04:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole world, not just the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.05,1:04:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most profitable, biggest corporation in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.20,1:04:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,based on spiritual principles.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.94,1:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that marvelous?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.12,1:04:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not exactly airy-fairy, airy-fairy.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.34,1:04:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So when people try to establish spiritual principles in business,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.84,1:04:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,don't call them spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.04,1:05:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't call them spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.08,1:05:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just say integrity pays off, and Walmart is a prime example.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.96,1:05:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see Enron and those companies
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.54,1:05:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,where the opposite was applied.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.82,1:05:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.42,1:05:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the validity, then, of integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.98,1:05:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as the basis of everyday practical life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.66,1:05:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we move on up to acceptance,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.70,1:05:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a very comfortable thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.10,1:05:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and reason and the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.90,1:05:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So America calibrates around 425, 431, around there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.79,1:05:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the world of reason and the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.73,1:05:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also the reason of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.22,1:05:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.10,1:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect will take you as far as Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.10,1:05:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein calibrates at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.25,1:05:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, who invented the differential calculus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.85,1:05:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Newtonian paradigm of reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.45,1:05:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the home of causality, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.69,1:05:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.39,1:06:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Isaac Newton, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.91,1:06:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sigmund Freud, 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.80,1:06:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's pushing the intellect as far as you can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.24,1:06:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pushing the intellect as far as you can go.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.58,1:06:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened with Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.56,1:06:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,then, was at the Solvay Conference,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.84,1:06:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Copenhagen, on quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.19,1:06:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem was facing the implication,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.15,1:06:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the metaphysical, philosophic implication
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.65,1:06:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.25,1:06:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery that on the microscopic,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.53,1:06:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,submicroscopic level,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.57,1:06:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that merely observation already changes the result.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.87,1:06:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The introduction of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.91,1:06:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,already changes the result,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.93,1:06:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,collapses the wave function,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.11,1:06:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and brings,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.69,1:06:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,out a new reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.60,1:06:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the potentiality becomes an actuality,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.86,1:06:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the trigger is merely human observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.32,1:06:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, there was all the big leading people,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.01,1:06:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, theoretical physics, Bohm,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.19,1:06:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the people there.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.06,1:07:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And Einstein said,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.25,1:07:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, what we're talking about is a paradigm jump.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.49,1:07:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein said, I prefer to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.63,1:07:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an observable, verifiable, objective world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.72,1:07:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.02,1:07:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists independent of human observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.76,1:07:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Independent.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.82,1:07:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, he sealed himself off at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.82,1:07:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the jump to 500 is a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.74,1:07:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They are jumping from the objective to the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.95,1:07:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,See, love is subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.71,1:07:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove love.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.91,1:07:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't measure love.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.89,1:07:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So the scientific dictum that if you can't measure it or weigh it,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.07,1:07:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't real, you know, is idiotic, right, on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.25,1:07:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's a subjective concept.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.65,1:07:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a subjective conclusion on the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.91,1:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's radical subjectivity to assume that some proposition is true.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.67,1:08:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the beginning of spiritual reality, as we understand it,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.05,1:08:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates 500 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.91,1:08:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of the kitty purr.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.95,1:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The domain of the wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.97,1:08:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The domain of the wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.56,1:08:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Rare is the individual in our world who calibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.14,1:08:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.08,1:08:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Four percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.80,1:08:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Four percent of humanity calibrates 500 or over.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.86,1:08:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Four percent of all the people on this earth ever get to consciousness level 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.45,1:08:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Love at 500 is still conditional.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.57,1:08:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dog will love just about everybody, but occasionally he won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.41,1:08:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a little bit conditional.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.91,1:08:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he'd calibrate at 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.13,1:08:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.38,1:08:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.80,1:08:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love, then, is practically saintly.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.42,1:09:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It is, oddly enough, 540 is a calibrated level of AA and all the 12-step programs.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.70,1:09:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.81,1:09:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A guy in AA goes out and gets drunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.95,1:09:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He drives over four people, destroys his car, burns down the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.39,1:09:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes back to a meeting, and they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.49,1:09:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,George, we're sure glad you're back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.11,1:09:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, only one concern.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.46,1:09:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's this man's spiritual recovery.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.86,1:09:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Period.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.56,1:09:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All the rest.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.66,1:09:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They leave for the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.04,1:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And A Course in Miracles, of course, calibrates at 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.22,1:09:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So 500 is extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.92,1:09:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,540, 0.4% of the world's population ever reaches 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.37,1:09:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,By 570, we consider them saints.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.11,1:09:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Pio, all the great spiritual writers, Dalai Lama, the Pope, all those people are in 570, around in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.70,1:09:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We consider them saintly.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.70,1:09:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To transcend saintliness, then, is another dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.74,1:10:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it takes one to 600, in which the mind is transcended altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.56,1:10:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything becomes silent, beatific.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.98,1:10:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One is outside time, space, dimension, position.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.20,1:10:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.76,1:10:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the world and karmically...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.02,1:10:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically is actually a karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.28,1:10:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If the body is destined to continue, then friendly...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.94,1:10:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,People and supportive beings will appear that encourage you to hang into the body, and feed it, and clothe it, and all kinds of things that they seem to be interested in.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.05,1:10:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.71,1:10:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, 50% of the people, once they hit 600, will leave the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.36,1:10:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you've ever gone to a bliss state, you realize how easy that would be.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.52,1:10:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've been in a divine state, you know that whether it continues or not is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.58,1:10:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the experience...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.48,1:11:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience is beyond physicality, and one loses one's interest in the world of appearance, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.42,1:11:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,600 is extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.10,1:11:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One in 10 million people, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.02,1:11:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The other odd thing that happens at 600...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.32,1:11:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, not really quite at 600, but 600 or over, is the recall of past lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.26,1:11:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no longer identification with this physicality or the mind, because you think...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.65,1:11:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think my life, what you mean is...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.53,1:11:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The memory of this body, and this fixed quantum of mentation, when you stop identifying with the physicality and the mind, when you're beyond mind and body, then all the lifetimes are one lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.34,1:11:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And significant events happen in each one of profound spiritual implication, and those you remember, because they were powerful lessons.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.76,1:11:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.88,1:12:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That life went that way, was to learn that lesson, to learn that you are a spirit, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.50,1:12:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at the oars of a slave ship, in a state of agony and semi-starvation and dehydration, in a stench that's unbelievable, under extreme cruelty, you suddenly get, you don't have to be trapped, you're not a prisoner, you can just leave the body and die.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.44,1:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wham!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.92,1:12:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of body.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.42,1:12:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of body.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.92,1:12:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.00,1:12:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought you were caught in an endless torture chamber.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.58,1:12:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.34,1:12:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you realize that you could just let the body die, and you're free of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.36,1:12:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.53,1:12:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell old people that in the nursing homes all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.63,1:12:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They call me in, tell them it's okay to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.81,1:12:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.84,1:13:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the psychiatrist for all the nursing homes in the county, because there wasn't any other psychiatrist who's willing to do it, to go and see all these old people.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.30,1:13:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd be going back to the nursing home, and they'd be saying, here's the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.78,1:13:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,people going back and forth in a wheelchair,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.62,1:13:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,help, help, help, help.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.12,1:13:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I look at her and I say,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.96,1:13:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, what's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.78,1:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Help, help, and you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.40,1:13:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't let me die.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.96,1:13:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's against Medicare regulations
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.76,1:13:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to let a patient die.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.13,1:13:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to please pull all these tubes out
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.17,1:13:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me be in peace, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.67,1:13:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as she goes off in peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.79,1:13:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they stick some more tubes
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.81,1:13:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and pump some more things in her
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.21,1:13:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and force her to keep breathing and yeah, so.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.83,1:13:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so then the higher levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.97,1:13:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of course, are traditional throughout history
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.71,1:13:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're extremely rare.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.93,1:13:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of those people do not stay around.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.41,1:13:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who reach like 700 and on
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.47,1:13:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,seldom become teachers or anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.51,1:13:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They usually withdraw from the world
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.91,1:13:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if they continue to exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.75,1:13:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And rarely do they come to the attention of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.15,1:14:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ability to speak, the ability to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.88,1:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And when such a state comes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.32,1:14:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it's necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.12,1:14:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to really leave the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.46,1:14:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can relate to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.89,1:14:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you can say about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.43,1:14:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way to describe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.65,1:14:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to describe.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.48,1:14:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The profound change cannot be communicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.42,1:14:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So usually nothing is said about it at all,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.70,1:14:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,except through accidentally getting dragged back
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.24,1:14:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,into the world to speak of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.88,1:14:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So those are the ineffable states.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.98,1:14:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The transcending of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.46,1:14:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we want to really address that more intensely.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.46,1:14:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we have sort of a map of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.76,1:14:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell us where we're going.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.80,1:14:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's go on to the next one then.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.02,1:14:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to show the distribution of the levels
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.08,1:14:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness in mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.38,1:14:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So the population of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.42,1:14:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the population of the world, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.86,1:15:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To reach 1,000 is, one person to 1,000 is,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.74,1:15:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalances the entire negativity over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.87,1:15:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,200 or one or two at 700 counterbalances
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.67,1:15:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the total negativity of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.11,1:15:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Two or three here counterbalances all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.31,1:15:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you see, here's the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.85,1:15:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 200, but less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.95,1:15:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great mass of mankind then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.09,1:15:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the mass of mankind is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.08,1:15:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's where most Americans live,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.94,1:15:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where an audience like this lives right about in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.22,1:15:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see how few in number they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.25,1:15:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But collectively, the people in this realm
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.85,1:15:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,are also counterbalancing the negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.49,1:15:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if it weren't for those
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.70,1:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of a higher level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.80,1:15:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that the world's population would self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.70,1:16:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the power of these people though,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.00,1:16:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,see these calibrated levels are,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.00,1:16:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,decimal, I mean are logarithm to base 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.66,1:16:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These are logarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.16,1:16:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the increase of one point here,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.40,1:16:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite sizable because it's the logarithm
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.70,1:16:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,of going up to the base 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.38,1:16:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the power of these people is so enormous
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.60,1:16:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that they can counterbalance the mass of these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.28,1:16:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are massive in number,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.34,1:16:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are deficient in power.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.16,1:16:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, only a few individuals then,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.28,1:16:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who are spiritually evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.36,1:16:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,are already counterbalancing huge numbers of people
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.82,1:16:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at the other end of the spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.82,1:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.48,1:16:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.36,1:16:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about duality,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.78,1:16:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,transcending good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.90,1:16:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a very difficult one.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.18,1:16:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand how the ego works then,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.28,1:17:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it adopts a positionality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.42,1:17:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a position about something,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.88,1:17:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and once you take a position about something,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.92,1:17:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you've now divided the world into the opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.06,1:17:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The polarities of good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.72,1:17:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,hot and cold, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.94,1:17:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As we tried to explain early this morning then,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.07,1:17:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,by seeing it differently,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.71,1:17:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you can transcend the opposites
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.51,1:17:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that there are no such things as opposites,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.65,1:17:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's actually only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.23,1:17:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As an example, let's take hot and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.53,1:17:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, hot and cold are opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.57,1:17:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we put them all on the same scale,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.21,1:17:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see there are not two opposites of hot and cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.31,1:17:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only the presence of heat or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.99,1:17:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.99,1:17:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the presence of heat.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.46,1:17:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Get lots of heat, we call it hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.69,1:17:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,As the heat goes down, the temperature goes down,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.05,1:18:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not into two opposites now.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.09,1:18:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat is not the opposite of cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.51,1:18:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is not its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.61,1:18:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is merely a designation for convenience.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.75,1:18:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable present.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.13,1:18:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In all dualistic seeming polarities,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.58,1:18:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,there are not two opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.98,1:18:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.62,1:18:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you see the one variable,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.78,1:18:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize you can dissolve the so-called polarity
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.92,1:18:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the opposites, which is the great blockade to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.92,1:18:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Classically, the great blockade to enlightenment is getting stuck
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.50,1:18:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the polarity of the opposites,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.96,1:18:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,seeming polarity of the opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.44,1:18:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll use another system.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.98,1:18:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You say things are good and things are worthless.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.28,1:18:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are good and bad and awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.91,1:18:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.11,1:18:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We skipped that one in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.47,1:18:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,On this one, we've got varying degrees of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.15,1:18:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.15,1:18:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to do that one?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.15,1:18:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.78,1:18:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you have desirability.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.52,1:19:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.78,1:19:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we value a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.56,1:19:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable, and that's our desire for that thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.56,1:19:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are not good and bad, desirable and repulsive.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.40,1:19:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You either desire them or you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.70,1:19:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You may consider swallowing the entrails of a spiny creature
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.90,1:19:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of the sea, whether that's a delicacy
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.06,1:19:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or repulsive.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.40,1:19:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on your viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.60,1:19:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that spiny black thing at the bottom of the sea?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.21,1:19:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The black, spiny thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.79,1:19:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is, anyway, some parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.68,1:19:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,swallowing its intestines is a great delicacy,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.82,1:19:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and it makes other people nauseated to think of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.44,1:19:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, is it precious, valuable, worthwhile?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.72,1:19:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we pay a lot of money for it on our sushi dinner
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.16,1:19:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever you call that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.12,1:19:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it repulsive?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.26,1:19:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, okay, let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.60,1:19:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.48,1:20:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the next one, we have the presence of love or not, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.10,1:20:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either there's the presence of love
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.14,1:20:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or there's not the presence of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.00,1:20:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There either is love or not love.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.65,1:20:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,On the right-hand side, you see there are not opposites
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.55,1:20:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of light and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.89,1:20:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are not opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.95,1:20:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we're showing you how to transcend good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.49,1:20:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the tough one, but once you see the paradigm here,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.29,1:20:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see light is present or not present to varying degrees,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.13,1:20:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but there isn't a thing called light.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.53,1:20:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no light against a thing called darkness, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.53,1:20:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see there's only one variable, light.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.86,1:20:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There's lots of it or not so much of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.68,1:20:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and lots of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.76,1:20:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we turn the light down.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.42,1:20:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, so there are no real opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.65,1:20:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because we give language to a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.19,1:20:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we think it must exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.73,1:20:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the problem of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.93,1:20:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why one can't become enlightened through the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.27,1:21:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but only by transcending the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.69,1:21:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because the intellect will always, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.97,1:21:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,propose something and then project it in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.73,1:21:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and think that it exists in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.67,1:21:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It, you know, causality is an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.43,1:21:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.57,1:21:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an intellectualization.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.53,1:21:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists only as a mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.76,1:21:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can find any causality in the universe anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.86,1:21:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't exist out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.50,1:21:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a concept projected onto, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.12,1:21:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an important jump in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.22,1:21:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because there you shift paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.97,1:21:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from form and structure,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.24,1:21:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the limitation of the ego in the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.84,1:21:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to move into subjective reality
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.60,1:21:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because the absolute reality that people are looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.60,1:21:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in all spiritual work is completely subjective.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.42,1:21:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why theology calibrates in the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.18,1:22:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Theology will take you through the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.46,1:22:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,philosophy and theology, and the answer is the conundrums.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.46,1:22:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I have all the great books
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.92,1:22:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Western world at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.56,1:22:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They calibrate around 465.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.68,1:22:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to the enigmas of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.34,1:22:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and divinity cannot be found through the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.38,1:22:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They can be talked about.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.26,1:22:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So theology calibrates around 465.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.92,1:22:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.38,1:22:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that here.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.78,1:22:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Theology as a science calibrates over 460, 465, 470, 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.66,1:22:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, epistemology calibrates over 475, 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.78,1:22:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Epistemology, hmm, well, the answer is that theology,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.78,1:22:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, philosophy takes you into theology,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.67,1:22:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and then theology, you hit dead ends,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.89,1:22:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and the answers then take you into epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.43,1:23:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Epistemology is how does man know in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.83,1:23:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.43,1:23:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the riddles that have baffled the world
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.47,1:23:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,are the ones that are the most important to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.43,1:23:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.63,1:23:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They baffle the philosophers over the centuries, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.23,1:23:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, you run up against,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.31,1:23:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,well, how do we even know anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.17,1:23:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that anything?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.47,1:23:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that we know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.07,1:23:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that is the question of epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.25,1:23:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We see it calibrates around 475.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.29,1:23:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the answer is really by revelation, subjectively.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.89,1:23:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you transcend to the next paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.19,1:23:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to leave the intellect altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.10,1:23:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to, you cannot prove the kiddies' fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.18,1:23:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove the doggies' wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.18,1:23:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove love and compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.26,1:23:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove why you stop and turn a little beetle
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.32,1:23:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,over on his feet so he can get going again
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.36,1:23:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,before the sun comes out and shrivels him up.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.79,1:24:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you suddenly care about that little black beetle?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.72,1:24:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, you don't really care.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.26,1:24:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that you care about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.78,1:24:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's an attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.24,1:24:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that that's the kind of being you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.27,1:24:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So 500,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.71,1:24:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what love really means then.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.35,1:24:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is not an emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.71,1:24:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes from here to there, from me to you,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.95,1:24:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore it's vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.91,1:24:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If love is just an emotion,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.89,1:24:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,then you end up with homicide and suicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.85,1:24:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the setup, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.20,1:24:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If it goes from here to there,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.74,1:24:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,well, you don't own it, now it's vulnerable,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.88,1:24:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other person can say bye now,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.04,1:24:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.54,1:24:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Or whoever persuaded them to leave you,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.64,1:24:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to kill them both, better, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.32,1:24:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end of that, you have to kill yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.32,1:24:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that, there's the whole human tragedy
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.42,1:24:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,without which we couldn't have any operas.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.82,1:24:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to all the operas and watch all the,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.96,1:25:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we love you, sweetheart, out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.46,1:25:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they go through the agony and the jealousy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.64,1:25:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they all stab themselves, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.80,1:25:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the curtain comes down, dun, dun, dun, dun.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.59,1:25:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Encapsulates.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.63,1:25:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the whole human tragedy, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.71,1:25:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what happens as a result of spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.31,1:25:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and dedication,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.15,1:25:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you become the love of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.40,1:25:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, love is a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.46,1:25:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.96,1:25:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not what you do, it's not what you feel,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.48,1:25:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.56,1:25:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of what you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.04,1:25:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you turn the little black beetle over, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.18,1:25:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that you love them, and if you get squashed,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.30,1:25:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not gonna grieve.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.62,1:25:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you might.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.86,1:25:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be a little black beetle,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.48,1:25:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you catch yourself emotionalizing about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.12,1:25:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you disconnect from that, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.00,1:25:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, love is not an attachment,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.20,1:25:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a way of being in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.24,1:26:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.62,1:26:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a necessary part of the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.86,1:26:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to become enlightened,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.62,1:26:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ultimate realization is God is allness,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.41,1:26:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.80,1:26:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to see that at this point, because,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.94,1:26:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important to see that at this point, because,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.38,1:26:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important to see that at this point, because,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.98,1:26:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,there are certain branches of Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.52,1:26:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which I am at liberty to speak of having been there,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.86,1:26:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,they will teach that love is another attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.53,1:26:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, emotional love as an attachment is a hindrance,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.59,1:26:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but love as a way of being, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.67,1:26:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,love is one of the attributes of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.03,1:26:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you negate the divinity of love,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.30,1:26:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you end up in the void,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.79,1:26:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've been in the void, it's very, very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.96,1:26:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the void was real,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.60,1:26:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be here to tell you about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.25,1:27:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The void is not the ultimate,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.11,1:27:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the pathway of negation, negation then,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.39,1:27:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,has a zinger in it, you gotta watch it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.22,1:27:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the infinite allness of existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.13,1:27:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest arises the manifest,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.83,1:27:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,arises consciousness, arises all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.44,1:27:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the allness out of which all arises
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.74,1:27:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and has its existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.78,1:27:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I understand the void,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.46,1:27:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the void calibrates about 900 and something or other,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.40,1:27:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is extremely impressive,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.32,1:27:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,except you can't stay there.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.13,1:27:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you come back the next lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.86,1:27:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,still in the void of nothingness, bang,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.82,1:27:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly confronted with existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.97,1:27:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You still haven't handled it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.17,1:27:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not beyond existence versus non-existence
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.65,1:27:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.61,1:28:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's where this lifetime started at age three.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.59,1:28:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of oblivion, absolute oblivion,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.91,1:28:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,void, nothingness, suddenly there was a shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.88,1:28:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Like out of the darkness,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.08,1:28:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all of a sudden all the light's going on,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.71,1:28:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm shocked with existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.30,1:28:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A three-year-old doesn't know the word existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.18,1:28:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't think existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.38,1:28:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But the knowingness of existence as existence
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.64,1:28:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,was like a shock, profound confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.34,1:28:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not happy with it either.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.58,1:28:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not happy with being confronted
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.18,1:28:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with existence at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.60,1:28:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I voided it out, and here I am confronted with it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.08,1:28:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as existence was faced as an experiential reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.24,1:28:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it was an experiential reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.24,1:28:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly the fear of non-existence came up.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.37,1:28:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you exist, it could have come about
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.79,1:29:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would not have existed.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.64,1:29:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there was the duality of existence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.04,1:29:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,versus non-existence as the ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.58,1:29:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Another conundrum, the Calvary said 850 to resolve,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.93,1:29:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and it took 50 years to do it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.61,1:29:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's interesting how life starts right out
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.38,1:29:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,with the unfinished spiritual business that you're left with.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.86,1:29:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it's the confrontation of the next life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.50,1:29:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we've handled now
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.06,1:29:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the most difficult dualities to be faced,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.46,1:29:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and we handled them early in the game instead of late.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.84,1:29:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason we did is we wanted to take their structure
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.14,1:29:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,out from underneath them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.18,1:29:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The structure is the belief that things are the opposites
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.44,1:29:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of each other, which is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.42,1:29:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a mental positionality, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.24,1:30:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one variable.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.64,1:30:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now we've handled good versus evil and existence
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.58,1:30:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,versus non-existence, so as you get close to the door
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.82,1:30:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of enlightenment, these will not come up and hit you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.08,1:30:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.13,1:30:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.17,1:30:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.87,1:30:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We said it's based on positionalities,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.07,1:30:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it tends to become enamored of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.89,1:30:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The interesting thing about the mind, people say,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.01,1:30:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,well, to become enlightened or to become very spiritually evolved,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.25,1:30:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's necessary to transcend the mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.25,1:30:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,first to educate the mind about spiritual matters,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.02,1:30:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but eventually you realize you're confronted
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.62,1:30:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with having to transcend it all altogether.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.78,1:30:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mind is structured then on certain positionalities,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.18,1:30:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and we tried to talk about the dualistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.38,1:30:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,polarities which are traditionally the blocks
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.62,1:31:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to enlightenment, how to transcend the mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.83,1:31:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we learned a lot of interesting things this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.47,1:31:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The next most interesting thing, and all the things
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.31,1:31:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that I tell you are gratifying and things to make you happy,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.05,1:31:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so you'll be real happy on the way home,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.31,1:31:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is that 99% of your mind is already silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.10,1:31:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You will think, how am I going to quiet this mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.06,1:31:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I meditate and it just chatters on and on.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.76,1:31:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-nine percent of your mind, or is it 98%?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.86,1:31:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-nine percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.60,1:31:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh, is it 98% or 99%?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.14,1:31:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-nine percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.80,1:31:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I wrote 98%.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.38,1:31:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, 98% of your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.40,1:31:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you think when you listen to your mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.46,1:31:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're meditating and it's thinking about this,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.46,1:31:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,imaging that, remembering that, and anticipating that,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.90,1:31:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can't seem to get your mind to be silent,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.50,1:31:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and people become very frustrated and they give up meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.70,1:32:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's very frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.10,1:32:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All I do is just sit there and think my thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.34,1:32:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which I do anyway when I'm driving,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.94,1:32:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm wasting time and I'm not going to be a good Buddhist anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.30,1:32:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like fish, and I don't like hamburgers,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.40,1:32:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I like killing bugs, so I'm a lousy Buddhist, give up.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.98,1:32:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can become a Unitarian or join Unity, it's coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.15,1:32:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.49,1:32:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This seeming horror.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.59,1:32:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a horrible block to enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.77,1:32:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going on with this?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.75,1:32:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are all kinds of tomes and great establishments
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.55,1:32:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to meditation and meditation techniques
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.27,1:32:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,with fancy sounding names, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.47,1:32:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is, if you look at mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.65,1:32:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if you look at your mind right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.61,1:32:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you one fact about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.27,1:32:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-eight percent of your mind is already silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.63,1:33:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one or two percent of your mind is thinking at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.46,1:33:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happened is that you're focused on this one or two percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.74,1:33:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're in a giant empty auditorium,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.24,1:33:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a giant stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:10.32,1:33:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one or two percent of your mind is thinking at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.10,1:33:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happened is that you're focused on this one or two percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.60,1:33:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're in a giant empty auditorium,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.10,1:33:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a giant stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.10,1:33:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's gone home.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.76,1:33:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the only one there, and way over in the corner,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.84,1:33:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a four-by-five-inch old black and white TV,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.44,1:33:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're glued to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.60,1:33:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only action.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.48,1:33:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing going on around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.78,1:33:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you say, boy, this is a noisy stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.46,1:33:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no noise in the stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.86,1:33:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you're glued to this little four-by-five-inch
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.32,1:33:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,black and white TV set.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.32,1:33:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so now I'll give you another secret truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.56,1:33:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is that you're hypnotized by the one percent.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.74,1:33:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ninety-eight percent of your mind is silent,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.94,1:34:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll demonstrate it to you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.34,1:34:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one or two percent is active,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.68,1:34:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's happened is that you're the hypnotic victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.78,1:34:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have become hypnotized, and you're in a hypnotic state
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.82,1:34:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of this one or two percent,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.95,1:34:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in a hypnotic, post-hypnotic state of suggestion
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.99,1:34:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you think that you are the one percent that's going on
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.23,1:34:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the only program on the dial.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.51,1:34:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.51,1:34:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.37,1:34:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To merely know that, certain knowledge advances consciousness rapidly just by hearing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.22,1:34:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to know that you are not the victim of your mind, that 98% of your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.64,1:35:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so to know that you are merely in a hypnotic state.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.64,1:35:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This hypnotic state then is of the 1% that's going on in the corner,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.64,1:35:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which you then tend to identify with because it's the only program going on in this empty stadium.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.41,1:35:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to take apart causality this morning because that's going to become critical to know when you want to transcend mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.85,1:35:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks that one thought is causing another.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.42,1:35:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the mind thinks...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.32,1:35:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks that...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.57,1:35:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought dog chases cat up and then the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.41,1:36:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, because it believes in sequential causality, it thinks that each one of these things is causing the next thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.41,1:36:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.91,1:36:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks the mind...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.91,1:36:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the way the linear person believes the mind works.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.91,1:36:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've already taken out its underpinnings this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.80,1:36:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So that what I say next morning...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.80,1:36:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This will make sense to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.64,1:36:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks this is how it's working.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.64,1:36:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Buddha said the ultimate reality is realizable between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.52,1:36:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the best form of expression and I've told him so.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.58,1:36:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, Buddha buddy, here's the way I look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.54,1:36:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And he agreed, it's better.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.92,1:36:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, you got 2,000 years to think about it, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.88,1:36:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, 2,000 years is the only way you can think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.88,1:37:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you meditate like I did when I first read about Zen and started going to Zen Institute and all,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.88,1:37:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you start looking between these thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.88,1:37:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're waiting for between dog and cat and run up tree there's going to be a little space that you can see God through there.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.88,1:37:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to wait a long time, folks, because these flow so fast you can't get between them.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.13,1:37:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no space between the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.13,1:37:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.64,1:37:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And they do not occur this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.64,1:37:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they occur this way, you can't get between them, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.64,1:37:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How does thought really arise?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.06,1:37:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here's the deliverance from being dominated by the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.80,1:37:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Each thought, like creation, arises individually as a separate and individual creation out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.15,1:37:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of nothingness, out of the great void, which is not the ultimate reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.52,1:38:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which it was thought by some Hinyana Buddhist.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.32,1:38:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the void arises dog, arises cat, arises up, arises tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.32,1:38:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one, each concept is an original creation out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.22,1:38:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not created out of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.22,1:38:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not an endless string of billiard balls and you can't get between the two billiard balls.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.22,1:38:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dog comes up, then cat comes up, then up comes up, and then tree comes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.49,1:38:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.78,1:38:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of silence, each thought arises as an original creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.84,1:38:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watch your thinkingness, then, instead of watching for this linear sequence,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.51,1:38:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,saying, oh, God, please help me forget about how I let old Rover get hit by the car,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.54,1:39:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that's this whole long sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.30,1:39:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see that the thought is coming up piecemeal.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.30,1:39:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,First, this component, out of a silent nothingness void,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.30,1:39:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,arises this as an original creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.45,1:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If the basis of existence was causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.48,1:39:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you would not be able to interrupt the train of thought
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.48,1:39:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because the train of thought is continuous and goes on forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.84,1:39:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no break in a train of thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.08,1:39:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you can break through it is because this thought is not caused by this thought at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.08,1:39:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of these thoughts arises independently,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.08,1:39:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and from here down, the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.47,1:39:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, 99% of this mind is silent, empty,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.04,1:39:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and each thought now arises independently.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.32,1:40:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they take some kind of a meaningful form
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.82,1:40:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is because within consciousness there are certain designs,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.91,1:40:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,certain designs which have been made famous by an English scientist
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.71,1:40:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,whose name I can't think of at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.71,1:40:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The things before they exist within the physical domain
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.32,1:40:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,already exist within consciousness as a pattern waiting for expression.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.32,1:40:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it, Rupert Sheldrake's Morphic Fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.99,1:40:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the Morphic Fields then exist within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.15,1:40:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of silence, within consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.15,1:40:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a million patterns created by mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.21,1:40:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the potentiality for form exists
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.21,1:40:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and this already is like a blueprint of energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.21,1:40:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our karmic pattern.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.21,1:41:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And within consciousness, there is the potentiality of all these various forms.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.21,1:41:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so if you think you are this,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.69,1:41:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then you are in for a tough life,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.69,1:41:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is 99% of people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.69,1:41:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you realize that you are this,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.43,1:41:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then you realize your mind is silent
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.43,1:41:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because to go from silence into form
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.46,1:41:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,requires intention, intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.72,1:41:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you can catch that all thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.72,1:41:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of your personal intention to think
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.78,1:41:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because you become hypnotized and fascinated
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.48,1:41:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.84,1:41:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, you can catch this in meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.84,1:41:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can catch this in meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.03,1:41:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at a tone of music.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.03,1:41:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as a tone of music, as the note is struck,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.03,1:41:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it rises to your attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.03,1:42:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But as the note of music rises to your attention,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.03,1:42:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's already beginning to fall, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.03,1:42:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It only is at the peak for a split 10,000th of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.03,1:42:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No sooner has a tone of music become apparent to the ear
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.38,1:42:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,than it's already falling away.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.38,1:42:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So every experience can be viewed as a wave.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.48,1:42:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People who live in fear
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.20,1:42:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then are always trying to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.20,1:42:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the front of the wave.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.23,1:42:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience comes up and then it's gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.23,1:42:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are always trying to get one up on the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.23,1:42:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearful, they're constantly on guard, paranoid, fearful,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.23,1:42:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to control everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.23,1:42:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So they don't live in the joy of the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.23,1:42:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They live in the fear of the future
Dialogue: 0,1:42:47.23,1:42:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and constantly trying to control.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.23,1:42:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What will I say when he says this?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.23,1:42:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What will I wear? What will people think?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.48,1:42:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Which way shall I turn?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.48,1:42:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen if I run out of insurance?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.48,1:42:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they fire me?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.48,1:42:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They just live on the fear of the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.48,1:43:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So they're living in advance of the wave of reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.48,1:43:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you experience reality
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.48,1:43:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is only experiential on the crest of the wave
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.48,1:43:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're focused on the front of the wave, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.48,1:43:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People hang into the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.44,1:43:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other people who ruminate all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.44,1:43:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They never live on the crest of now
Dialogue: 0,1:43:21.44,1:43:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're always reworking what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.83,1:43:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have said this. I'll show that guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.83,1:43:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time he tries that with me,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.83,1:43:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.83,1:43:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trying to rewrite history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.83,1:43:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people busy in the academic world now
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.83,1:43:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are trying to rewrite history.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.04,1:43:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To live on the crest of the moment
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.04,1:43:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,means the willingness to relinquish
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.04,1:43:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the willfulness of editorializing about experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.32,1:43:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The human's will is to editorialize,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.44,1:44:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly change shape and control the experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.70,1:44:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Either try to fool reality by anticipating it
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.70,1:44:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or refuse to let go of it by clinging to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:10.70,1:44:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So the technique of meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:44:15.33,1:44:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that brings you into an awareness of the presence as silence
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.33,1:44:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness to surrender each thing as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.65,1:44:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrenderingness is as each thing peaks into awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.07,1:44:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As it arises, we surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.07,1:44:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.07,1:44:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,everything to God as it comes into awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.07,1:44:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if you keep doing that,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.29,1:44:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you get earlier and earlier in the pattern of thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.29,1:44:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to catch it here at Sheldrakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.29,1:44:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.29,1:44:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't think of his name at this point.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.48,1:44:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to catch it here as it begins to take form.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.48,1:44:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As it begins to take form.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.48,1:45:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because thoughts are not unlike the rest of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.57,1:45:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Each species, each genus comes off the evolutionary branch.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.18,1:45:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Separately.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.18,1:45:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see links between the various branches.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.50,1:45:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes off as this and then it comes off as that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.88,1:45:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't see any evolutionary half-zebra, half-horse.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.88,1:45:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.88,1:45:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The zebra comes off, the horse comes off.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.88,1:45:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Neanderthal man comes off, magnetoman comes off.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.72,1:45:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't see evolution as a slow progression
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.78,1:45:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,from one genus and species into another.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.78,1:45:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is the advancement on the stem of life energy itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.88,1:45:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It emerges as this and then more advanced as this
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.88,1:45:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then more advanced as that.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.88,1:45:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So homo sapien is not an improvement on chromomagnon man.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.67,1:45:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's something different.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.67,1:46:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not an improvement on Neanderthal man.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.67,1:46:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see Neanderthal man slowly becoming homo sapien.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.67,1:46:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.67,1:46:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one comes off separately.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:12.40,1:46:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is a different expression of Sheldrake's morphogenetic field.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.50,1:46:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolution occurs on the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.50,1:46:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it manifests out as an expression of the form
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.60,1:46:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that is held within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.60,1:46:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So the evolution of form then happens on the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.60,1:46:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then expresses itself within the manifest, visible,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.60,1:46:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.65,1:46:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That brings up an interesting conundrum,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.81,1:46:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,which I haven't figured out yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.81,1:46:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was the mother of the first human being,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.81,1:46:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the first homo sapien?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.06,1:46:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if each branch doesn't become the next branch,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.06,1:47:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there's a new branch called homo sapien.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.06,1:47:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was the mother of the first human being?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.16,1:47:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't an ape because evolution doesn't occur out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.16,1:47:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It occurs on the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.11,1:47:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do we humans even get ourselves born?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.16,1:47:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, not only are we born, but we've got no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.93,1:47:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Seventy man finds himself born with no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.19,1:47:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell do you do?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.19,1:47:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No clothes and no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.25,1:47:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No hooves.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.25,1:47:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you walk across the desert with these kind of feet?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.25,1:47:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.37,1:47:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't climb rocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.56,1:47:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What can he do?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:38.56,1:47:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn't got wings to fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.56,1:47:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a pathetic creature, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.56,1:47:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Stark naked, no fur, no wings, no claws.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.60,1:47:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No big teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.60,1:47:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No hooves.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.60,1:47:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're supposed to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.60,1:47:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:51.88,1:47:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We were the losers in some big crap game, weren't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:57.20,1:47:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You get no fur.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.20,1:47:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You get no clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.20,1:48:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You get no money when you get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.20,1:48:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No hooves, no paws.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:02.20,1:48:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No friends, no mama, no daddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.68,1:48:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.58,1:48:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we're trying to transcend the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.47,1:48:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Things I'm saying are not irrelevant to the ultimate conclusion,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.47,1:48:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which is your enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.47,1:48:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because these are the blocks which prevent it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.47,1:48:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The belief in duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.47,1:48:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not realizing that just holding on to a positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.47,1:48:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is creating all the noise in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.47,1:48:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking that your confrontation is that you have to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.47,1:48:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,this entire mind where you don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.47,1:48:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,98% of your mind is gone already.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.47,1:48:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the good news.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:41.50,1:48:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.50,1:48:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you watch your mind, then you will see
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.50,1:48:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that thoughts are originating out of silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.50,1:48:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.69,1:48:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at your mind right now,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.69,1:48:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,picture your mind as sort of a space here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.69,1:48:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see the thinkingness is going on at the very front.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.69,1:48:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Words, thinkingness, images, all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.69,1:49:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right behind all that is really sort of a feelingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.84,1:49:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But then behind all that is really nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.84,1:49:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There's really primarily silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.84,1:49:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which a little wispy thought starts to come out.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.88,1:49:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you encourage it, it'll gain some control.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.88,1:49:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't encourage it, it'll back down again.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.00,1:49:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can actually catch the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:22.00,1:49:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll catch the source of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.00,1:49:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.00,1:49:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an energy field within the void itself
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.00,1:49:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whose narcissistic goal is its own continuation,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.44,1:49:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does so by energizing thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.44,1:49:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're hooked on and hypnotized by
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.44,1:49:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is the thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.05,1:49:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, hypnotic states can be undone.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:49.05,1:49:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you realize they are a hypnotic state,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.05,1:49:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they cannot be undone if you just think that's reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.15,1:49:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But once you realize, and the doctor tells you,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.44,1:50:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you've all been hypnotized without your conscious assent,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.53,1:50:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're in a position to begin to undo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.53,1:50:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to know that you are not your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.53,1:50:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are hypnotized in a hypnotic state
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.53,1:50:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you believe that your thinkingness and thoughts are you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.84,1:50:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible for your thinkingness and your thoughts to be you,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:21.84,1:50:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or you'd be dead long ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.13,1:50:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that, if you weren't dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.13,1:50:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody would kill you for sure
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.13,1:50:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for what goes on in your thinkingness and your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.13,1:50:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.13,1:50:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, your thinkingness and your thoughts are not you,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:38.13,1:50:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,or you couldn't even be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.13,1:50:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you discover.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.13,1:50:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here's how the addiction to the thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.13,1:50:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,propagates itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.77,1:50:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Polarity means, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.09,1:50:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that we create a set of,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.09,1:51:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a set of opposites so that that sets up tension,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.09,1:51:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,contention,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.12,1:51:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and propagates the illusions of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.12,1:51:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The way we do this is we are addicted to politicizing things.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:11.12,1:51:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Politicizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.12,1:51:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't mention anything anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.12,1:51:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that doesn't get instantly politicized.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.12,1:51:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to either de-genderize everything
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.72,1:51:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or genderize it, depending on their political position.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.82,1:51:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, if you want to de-genderize everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:27.82,1:51:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to get into a foreign language
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.82,1:51:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where everything in the,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.82,1:51:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,every single word in the language has a gender.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.82,1:51:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The table, the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.82,1:51:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you use a feminine or masculine pronoun,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.82,1:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so how in the world are you going to de-genderize
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.82,1:51:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the language in which it is intrinsic to the language?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.98,1:51:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it moralizes about things,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.98,1:51:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or it idealizes,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.98,1:51:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothesizes.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.98,1:51:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the bases of death and destruction throughout history.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.98,1:51:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We politicize things,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.98,1:51:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we get out the machine guns.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.98,1:52:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We moralize they deserve to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:00.98,1:52:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't even feel guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.98,1:52:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We idealize what a nice world it would be if they were gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:07.98,1:52:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We hypothesize that they shouldn't be the way they are anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.98,1:52:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We romanticize what a nice world it would be
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.98,1:52:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if all the so-and-sos were off the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.98,1:52:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll help them get off the planet by one form or another.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.20,1:52:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The justification and the rationalization for this
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.22,1:52:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is to criticize.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.22,1:52:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we criticize.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.64,1:52:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We polarize.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.64,1:52:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We get ourselves in quite a state and emotionalize about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.73,1:52:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we dramatize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.73,1:52:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a drama.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.73,1:52:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a protest.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.73,1:52:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We parade with flags.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.76,1:52:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Down with the whatchamacallits.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.76,1:52:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Down with the professional protesters.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.76,1:52:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the FBI takes pictures of all these protests.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.76,1:52:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see people there at every protest about everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.76,1:52:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They have the sign at home that says down with,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.76,1:52:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and they leave that blank.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:55.76,1:52:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Put in there down with Clinton,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.76,1:52:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,down with Bush,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.76,1:53:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,down with animal rights,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.76,1:53:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,down with God knows what,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.76,1:53:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,down with dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:04.92,1:53:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And they tend to dramatize it
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.92,1:53:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and that justifies catastrophizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.92,1:53:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Catastrophizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.92,1:53:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society is now in a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.92,1:53:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society has been in a continuous catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.92,1:53:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,since man began.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.92,1:53:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Man's history is one continuous catastrophe
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.18,1:53:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if you look at it in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.18,1:53:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It started with a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.18,1:53:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No fur, no claws, no hoofs.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.18,1:53:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, no mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.18,1:53:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the human being's first mother?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.60,1:53:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish that everybody would puzzle on that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:34.60,1:53:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could be the first mother?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:36.85,1:53:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each one comes off as a new one.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.85,1:53:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So who is the first mother then
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.98,1:53:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,if it didn't evolve from a prior biped?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:43.98,1:53:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.98,1:53:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we theorize about it,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.40,1:53:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just as I'm doing right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.40,1:53:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we theorize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.40,1:53:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it could have been a...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.40,1:53:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we rationalize our behavior.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.40,1:53:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We fantasize.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.40,1:53:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We infantilize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.40,1:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society is greatly damaged.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.40,1:54:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is infantilizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:00.40,1:54:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is responsible for anything anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.48,1:54:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hit your head against the door,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.48,1:54:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you sue the doormaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.74,1:54:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If your building gets bombed,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.74,1:54:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you sue people that your building is bombable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.74,1:54:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the latest kick.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.77,1:54:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That your building is bombable.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.77,1:54:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.00,1:54:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you fantasize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.00,1:54:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You infantilize people.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.00,1:54:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You intellectualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.00,1:54:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to feel negative about things.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.00,1:54:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You intellectualize how right it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.00,1:54:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And you mentalize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.64,1:54:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We idealize twice.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.64,1:54:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We idealize twice because it's so important.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.67,1:54:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we glamorize.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:40.67,1:54:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be weird when they show up twice.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.70,1:54:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we glamorize everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.70,1:54:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the great world of the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.70,1:54:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The great media add to the hypnotic trance.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.70,1:54:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is in a hypnotic trance.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.70,1:54:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the media know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.70,1:54:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, you don't have to have any...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:57.70,1:55:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic dictum now is no reality is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.70,1:55:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's an impediment.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.56,1:55:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that it counts is the image.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.56,1:55:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The image that is the total message.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.56,1:55:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need any reality at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.63,1:55:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can create...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.63,1:55:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'll create a product right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.63,1:55:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.13,1:55:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Big red box.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.13,1:55:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hands coming out.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.13,1:55:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Children's hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.13,1:55:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.13,1:55:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it doesn't matter what you put in the box, does it?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.58,1:55:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Crunchies, creepies, pink and blue little crunchies.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.58,1:55:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter what you put in the box
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.58,1:55:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because you already got a product.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:32.58,1:55:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Your product is the grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.54,1:55:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.54,1:55:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams make you healthy.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:38.54,1:55:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Grabhams build better humans, Americans.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.54,1:55:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can build up a whole product called grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.54,1:55:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't even know what the product is yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.54,1:55:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last part of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:47.54,1:55:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get the whole production put together,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.54,1:55:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, what are we going to put in the box?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.54,1:55:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.54,1:55:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Put the little crunchy things.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.54,1:55:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the last minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.54,1:55:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't require...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.54,1:55:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can glamorize things.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:58.54,1:56:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful people eat grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.54,1:56:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong people eat grabhams.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.54,1:56:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,People with great abs.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.54,1:56:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Great abs.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.33,1:56:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,People with big biceps like mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.33,1:56:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,People with a full head of hair.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.79,1:56:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Demonizing is the specialty of the current media
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.79,1:56:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the one you really got to watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.79,1:56:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't seem to like vanilla without hating chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.33,1:56:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The current political bent, editorial bent is
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.33,1:56:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't just like something,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.33,1:56:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to hate the other one.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.00,1:56:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said last night,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.00,1:56:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that you love vanilla
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.00,1:56:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean you have to hate chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.00,1:56:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you like chocolate
Dialogue: 0,1:56:43.00,1:56:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean you have to hate vanilla.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:45.00,1:56:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell me what's great about your candidate.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:47.10,1:56:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to demonize the other one.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.10,1:56:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.10,1:56:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have anything good to say about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.10,1:56:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then all you can do is demonize the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:57.10,1:57:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,People spend all their time demonizing the opponent.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.41,1:57:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I say they must not have anything good to offer
Dialogue: 0,1:57:02.41,1:57:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because all they can do is knock the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.41,1:57:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But what have you got to offer?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:07.41,1:57:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.41,1:57:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your solution to man's problems?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.41,1:57:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And then they go silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.41,1:57:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have any.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:12.41,1:57:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we demonize.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.80,1:57:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We prize things and we seek them out.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.80,1:57:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, victimizing is of course
Dialogue: 0,1:57:20.80,1:57:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the great basis of current society.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:25.50,1:57:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything and everyone is the victim of something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.50,1:57:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have the world of perpetrator and victim
Dialogue: 0,1:57:33.60,1:57:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the ultimate expression
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.60,1:57:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the basic belief in causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.92,1:57:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you believe in causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:40.92,1:57:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there will always be a perpetrator and a victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.92,1:57:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you will never find the answer to anything
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.46,1:57:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because neither one is so.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:49.46,1:57:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are both imaginations projected out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.46,1:57:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The closest thing to the truth I've seen in the media then
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.62,1:58:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was the discovery of that headline
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.89,1:58:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that said that the accident of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.89,1:58:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call those spaceships?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.89,1:58:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.18,1:58:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuttle, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.18,1:58:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the consequence of the culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.18,1:58:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,now they're getting close.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:13.24,1:58:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the first thing I've heard that's close to reality
Dialogue: 0,1:58:16.24,1:58:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's crossed the public view.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:18.24,1:58:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:20.24,1:58:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the totality of the field that allows that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:24.24,1:58:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you're looking for Mr. X
Dialogue: 0,1:58:26.24,1:58:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,who forgot to screw in the jiggly thing so we can sue him,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:29.24,1:58:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you're never going to find it
Dialogue: 0,1:58:31.24,1:58:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's only the expression of the totality of the culture
Dialogue: 0,1:58:35.24,1:58:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which all of us grab a little from the till,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.31,1:58:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us scoop a little off the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:40.31,1:58:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:42.31,1:58:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the culture that allows that.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:44.31,1:58:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see whole societies and countries bogged down
Dialogue: 0,1:58:48.37,1:58:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the culture, the culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:53.20,1:58:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What went on in Chicago when I was a kid,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:57.26,1:59:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it still goes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.12,1:59:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but the culture, the culture allowed for certain variances
Dialogue: 0,1:59:05.60,1:59:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with what we would call the perfect ideal.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.60,1:59:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And somebody I knew,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:14.96,1:59:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to come down and see him in Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.96,1:59:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'd park right in front of the hydrant.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.19,1:59:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, hey, you're going to get a ticket.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:22.19,1:59:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, no, the cop and I are friends,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:24.19,1:59:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.19,1:59:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In that culture, at that time, in that neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:29.19,1:59:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the way things went, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:31.19,1:59:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way things went.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:33.19,1:59:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We see whole cultures in which that's how it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.19,1:59:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The police pull you over not because you're violating the law,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:40.44,1:59:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but because they got you and it's going to cost you to get off.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:44.44,1:59:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the judge knows that, so he gets a slice,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.86,1:59:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so God help you if you've been a defender in certain countries
Dialogue: 0,1:59:50.86,1:59:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's going to cost you plenty to get it back.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:53.86,1:59:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're under arrest for so and so,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:55.86,1:59:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the hand's out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.08,2:00:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's endemic to the culture.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.08,2:00:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the culture.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:01.08,2:00:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the whole space that allows that.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.08,2:00:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't him being a bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:05.08,2:00:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,doing a bad thing against a bad guy,
Dialogue: 0,2:00:07.08,2:00:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's causality.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:09.08,2:00:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the totality of the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:11.08,2:00:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we as spiritually evolving people then
Dialogue: 0,2:00:14.24,2:00:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,are actually changing the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.66,2:00:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're actually changing the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:18.66,2:00:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A field that went up from 190 to 207 is a different field.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.66,2:00:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In 207, you can't just comfortably pay off the local cops anymore.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:27.76,2:00:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.76,2:00:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He isn't comfortable about it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:30.76,2:00:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain lap over between the old way and the new way.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:33.76,2:00:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a period of discomfort.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.11,2:00:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The guys who are used to it the old way
Dialogue: 0,2:00:38.11,2:00:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to, you know, go against their old friends.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.11,2:00:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The new guys don't want to make it hard on the old guys.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:44.11,2:00:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get a sort of a painful adjustment
Dialogue: 0,2:00:47.11,2:00:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're lapping over from one culture
Dialogue: 0,2:00:49.11,2:00:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,into a new culture.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.13,2:00:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And people, opportunists, try to seize the new culture
Dialogue: 0,2:00:59.13,2:01:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and retrograde, project it against the old culture
Dialogue: 0,2:01:02.13,2:01:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and do a make wrong on what would happen in history.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:05.48,2:01:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened in history?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:07.48,2:01:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship of men and women
Dialogue: 0,2:01:09.48,2:01:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in our socioeconomic state is different in 2003
Dialogue: 0,2:01:13.96,2:01:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,than it was in 1930.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.96,2:01:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take the social structure of 2003
Dialogue: 0,2:01:21.92,2:01:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and go back to 1930 and say,
Dialogue: 0,2:01:23.92,2:01:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,look how wrong it was.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:25.92,2:01:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an agrarian, rural culture.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:29.44,2:01:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We all had our family roles
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.44,2:01:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the nature of society at that time.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:35.44,2:01:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,To take some political agenda
Dialogue: 0,2:01:37.98,2:01:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,projected backward in time and do a make wrong,
Dialogue: 0,2:01:39.98,2:01:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how you're no longer dealing in reality at all.
